1
00:02:27,898 --> 00:02:31,360
Command station, this is ST-321.
Code clearance blue.

2
00:02:31,485 --> 00:02:34,404
We’re starting our approach.
Deactivate the security shield.

3
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:39,826
The security deflector shield will be deactivated
when we have confirmation
of your code transmission.

4
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:40,953
Stand by.

5
00:02:42,496 --> 00:02:44,414
You are clear to proceed.

6
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:45,916
We’re starting our approach.

7
00:02:57,803 --> 00:03:01,849
[Siren]

8
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:16,864
Inform the commander
that Lord Vader’s shuttle has arrived.

9
00:03:16,989 --> 00:03:18,073
Sir.

10
00:03:54,151 --> 00:03:57,821
Lord Vader, this is an unexpected pleasure.
We’re honored by your presence.

11
00:03:57,905 --> 00:04:00,365
You may dispense
with the pleasantries, Commander.

12
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:02,784
I’m here to put you back on schedule.

13
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:06,163
I assure you, Lord Vader,
my men are working as fast as they can.

14
00:04:06,413 --> 00:04:09,708
Perhaps I can find new ways to motivate them.

15
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:14,004
I tell you this station
will be operational, as planned.

16
00:04:14,129 --> 00:04:19,801
The emperor does not share
your optimistic appraisal of the situation.

17
00:04:19,885 --> 00:04:23,430
But he asks the impossible.
I need more men.

18
00:04:23,514 --> 00:04:26,683
Then perhaps you can tell him
when he arrives.

19
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:28,936
The emperor’s coming here?

20
00:04:29,019 --> 00:04:31,438
That is correct, Commander,

21
00:04:31,563 --> 00:04:36,318
and he is most displeased
with your apparent lack of progress.

22
00:04:36,443 --> 00:04:38,904
We shall double our efforts.

23
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:42,324
I hope so, Commander, for your sake.

24
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:46,537
The emperor is not as forgiving as I am.

25
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,137
[Whistle Whistle Beep]

26
00:05:04,221 --> 00:05:06,223
Of course I’m worried.
And you should be, too.

27
00:05:06,473 --> 00:05:10,602
Lando Calrissian and poor Chewbacca
never returned from this awful place.

28
00:05:10,686 --> 00:05:12,938
[Beep Beep Whistle]

29
00:05:13,063 --> 00:05:14,690
Don’t be so sure.

30
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:19,820
If I told you half the things I’ve heard about
this Jabba the Hutt, you’d probably short-circuit.

31
00:05:19,903 --> 00:05:21,738
[Whining]

32
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:23,949
[Whistle Whistle]

33
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:32,999
[Beep Whistle]

34
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:36,003
R2, are you sure this is the right place?

35
00:05:36,128 --> 00:05:38,630
[Whistle Beep Beep]

36
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:41,258
I’d better knock, I suppose.

37
00:05:41,550 --> 00:05:42,676
[Whistle]

38
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,680
There doesn’t seem to be anyone here.
Let’s go back and tell Master Luke.

39
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:48,056
[Beep Beep]

40
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,518
[Speaking Huttese]

41
00:05:51,643 --> 00:05:53,770
Goodness gracious me!

42
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:55,856
[Speaking Huttese]

43
00:05:55,981 --> 00:05:58,483
R2-Dee Toa.

44
00:05:58,609 --> 00:06:00,360
[Whistle Beep]

45
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:01,778
[Speaking Huttese]

46
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:03,030
[Whistle Beep Whistle]

47
00:06:03,155 --> 00:06:05,073
[Speaking Huttese]

48
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:07,242
C-3POA.

49
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:11,038
Ay tuta mishka Jabba du Hutt?

50
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:15,626
Kuja wanki mitby cosa.

51
00:06:15,751 --> 00:06:16,752
Ha ha ha!

52
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:20,923
I don’t think they’re going to let us in, R2.

53
00:06:21,048 --> 00:06:23,550
We’d better go.

54
00:06:23,634 --> 00:06:25,552
[Rumble]

55
00:06:25,636 --> 00:06:27,137
[Creak]

56
00:06:27,221 --> 00:06:29,056
[Whistle]

57
00:06:29,139 --> 00:06:31,058
[Beep Whistle Beep]

58
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:33,060
R2, wait!

59
00:06:33,143 --> 00:06:34,686
[Whistle]

60
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:36,063
Oh, dear!

61
00:06:36,146 --> 00:06:37,523
R2!

62
00:06:37,648 --> 00:06:40,817
R2, I really don’t
think we should rush into all this.

63
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,069
[Beep Beep]

64
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:43,695
Oh! R2!

65
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:45,739
R2, wait for me!

66
00:06:45,864 --> 00:06:48,825
[Whistle Beep]

67
00:06:48,951 --> 00:06:49,910
Grr!

68
00:06:49,993 --> 00:06:50,869
[Beep Beep]

69
00:06:50,994 --> 00:06:52,788
Grr!

70
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:57,251
Just you deliver Master Luke’s message
and get us out of here. Oh, my!

71
00:06:57,334 --> 00:06:58,544
Oh!

72
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:03,131
Oh, no.

73
00:07:03,215 --> 00:07:04,550
[Speaking Huttese]

74
00:07:07,177 --> 00:07:08,595
Day wonna wonga?

75
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,930
Oh, my!

76
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:12,182
Dee wonna wygo.

77
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:13,725
[Beep]

78
00:07:13,851 --> 00:07:17,938
We bring a message
to your master Jabba the Hutt.

79
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:20,607
Day Jabba wonga?

80
00:07:20,732 --> 00:07:21,775
[Beep Beep]

81
00:07:21,859 --> 00:07:23,944
And a gift.

82
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:25,362
Gift? What gift?

83
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:27,197
[Beep Whistle]

84
00:07:27,322 --> 00:07:31,535
Ne Jabba no barta.

85
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:33,078
Eezai ohkto.

86
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:35,122
[Whistle Whistle]

87
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:36,790
Izzi kata o mohkti?

88
00:07:36,874 --> 00:07:38,125
[Beep Beep]

89
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:40,127
Ne charda so dehdi.

90
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:41,795
[Whistle Beep]

91
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:47,134
He says that our instructions
are to give it only to Jabba himself.

92
00:07:47,259 --> 00:07:51,138
[Whistle Whistle]

93
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:52,472
Grr!

94
00:07:52,598 --> 00:07:54,892
Grr!

95
00:07:57,019 --> 00:07:58,645
I’m terribly sorry.

96
00:07:58,729 --> 00:08:01,857
I’m afraid he’s ever so stubborn
about these sort of things.

97
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:03,025
Noht cha!

98
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:07,821
R2, I have a bad feeling about this.

99
00:08:07,905 --> 00:08:09,823
[Whistle]

100
00:08:10,073 --> 00:08:12,701
Oohh!

101
00:08:19,917 --> 00:08:21,210
Arf! Arf!

102
00:08:21,293 --> 00:08:23,253
Arf! Arf!

103
00:08:36,808 --> 00:08:38,810
Oohh!

104
00:08:38,894 --> 00:08:40,604
Cava notayce, my lord.

105
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:43,232
Good morning.

106
00:08:43,357 --> 00:08:45,817
Ohnt bat chuay dehr attat.

107
00:08:45,901 --> 00:08:47,736
Oohh!

108
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:50,739
The message, R2, the message.

109
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:53,575
Oohh shoodah.

110
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:57,204
[Whistle Whistle Beep]

111
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:02,459
Greetings, Exalted One.

112
00:09:02,709 --> 00:09:04,878
Allow me to introduce myself.

113
00:09:05,003 --> 00:09:06,380
I am Luke Skywalker,

114
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:08,882
Jedi knight
and friend to Captain Solo.

115
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:11,969
I know that you are powerful, mighty Jabba,

116
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:16,139
and that your anger with Solo
must be equally powerful.

117
00:09:16,265 --> 00:09:20,060
I seek an audience with Your Greatness
to bargain for Solo’s life.

118
00:09:20,185 --> 00:09:23,063
Ha ha ha!

119
00:09:23,188 --> 00:09:24,648
With your wisdom,

120
00:09:24,773 --> 00:09:28,318
I’m sure that we can
work out an arrangement
which will be mutually beneficial

121
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:33,031
and enable us to avoid
any unpleasant confrontation.

122
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:36,869
As a token of my goodwill,
I present to you a gift-

123
00:09:36,952 --> 00:09:38,287
these two droids.

124
00:09:38,412 --> 00:09:40,289
What did he say?

125
00:09:40,414 --> 00:09:43,959
Both are hardworking and will serve you well.

126
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:45,252
This can’t be!

127
00:09:45,335 --> 00:09:47,880
R2, you’re playing the wrong message.

128
00:09:47,963 --> 00:09:48,797
Ha ha!

129
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:50,465
Ah ha ha ha!

130
00:09:50,591 --> 00:09:54,344
Master, bargonay tua knight?

131
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:57,139
He’s no Jedi.

132
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:02,686
[Speaking Huttese]
There will be no bargain.

133
00:10:02,811 --> 00:10:05,022
We’re doomed.

134
00:10:05,147 --> 00:10:12,196
I will not give up my favorite decoration.

135
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:17,117
I like Captain Solo where he is.

136
00:10:18,869 --> 00:10:20,829
R2, look- Captain Solo.

137
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:23,957
And he’s still frozen in carbonite.

138
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:25,083
[Whistle]

139
00:10:25,209 --> 00:10:26,543
Ah ha ha!

140
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:30,005
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

141
00:10:36,053 --> 00:10:38,972
What could possibly
have come over Master Luke?

142
00:10:39,056 --> 00:10:40,974
Was it something I did?

143
00:10:41,058 --> 00:10:44,102
He never expressed any
unhappiness with my work.

144
00:10:44,186 --> 00:10:46,980
Ohh! How horrid!

145
00:10:47,064 --> 00:10:48,357
Ohh!

146
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,983
Grr!

147
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:51,360
Grr!

148
00:10:51,485 --> 00:10:54,029
[Whistle Whistle]

149
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:06,333
Ah ah ah!

150
00:11:06,416 --> 00:11:08,961
Ah ah ha!

151
00:11:09,044 --> 00:11:10,963
Aaah!

152
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:17,594
Ah, good. New acquisitions.

153
00:11:17,845 --> 00:11:20,764
You are a protocol droid,
are you not?

154
00:11:20,889 --> 00:11:22,516
I am C-3PO-

155
00:11:22,599 --> 00:11:25,185
Yes or no will do.

156
00:11:25,269 --> 00:11:26,311
Oh. Well, yes.

157
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,939
How many languages do you speak?

158
00:11:29,064 --> 00:11:33,610
I am fluent in over six million forms
of communication and can-

159
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:35,904
Splendid. We have been
without an interpreter

160
00:11:35,988 --> 00:11:40,826
since our master got angry
with our last protocol droid
and disintegrated him.

161
00:11:40,951 --> 00:11:42,369
Disintegrated?

162
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:45,414
Aah!

163
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:47,457
Oh!

164
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:51,253
Guard!
This protocol droid might be useful.

165
00:11:51,378 --> 00:11:57,009
Fit him with a restraining bolt
and take him back up to His Excellency’s
main audience chamber.

166
00:11:57,134 --> 00:11:59,261
R2, don’t leave me!

167
00:11:59,344 --> 00:12:01,013
Oh!

168
00:12:01,138 --> 00:12:03,348
[Whistle Beep Bleep]

169
00:12:03,432 --> 00:12:06,185
You’re a feisty little one,

170
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:08,645
but you’ll soon learn some respect.

171
00:12:08,896 --> 00:12:12,232
I have need for you on
the master’s sail barge,

172
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:16,111
and I think you’ll fill in nicely.

173
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:19,573
No! No! No!

174
00:12:19,656 --> 00:12:20,991
Aaahh!

175
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:24,411
[Singing In Huttese]

176
00:12:44,348 --> 00:12:47,684
Ah! Do that again!

177
00:12:47,976 --> 00:12:50,020
[Singing In Huttese]

178
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:58,028
[Singing In Huttese]

179
00:13:06,203 --> 00:13:07,871
Ho ho!

180
00:13:47,703 --> 00:13:49,162
Aah!

181
00:13:49,288 --> 00:13:50,372
Whoops! Uh-oh!

182
00:13:50,497 --> 00:13:52,040
Aah!

183
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:58,505
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

184
00:14:00,424 --> 00:14:02,426
[Creaking]

185
00:14:05,304 --> 00:14:07,306
[Beast Growls]

186
00:14:07,431 --> 00:14:09,474
Aaaah!

187
00:14:12,394 --> 00:14:14,104
[Squeals]

188
00:14:21,236 --> 00:14:22,196
[Zap]

189
00:14:23,572 --> 00:14:25,324
Ooahhh!

190
00:14:26,617 --> 00:14:28,160
Aah!

191
00:14:29,161 --> 00:14:30,162
[Speaking Huttese]

192
00:14:30,245 --> 00:14:31,371
Uhh!

193
00:14:41,173 --> 00:14:45,302
[Speaking Ubese]
I have come for the bounty on this Wookiee.

194
00:14:45,427 --> 00:14:48,555
Oh, no. Chewbacca!

195
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,557
Aarrrrr.

196
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:55,979
[Speaking Huttese]
At last we have the mighty Chewbacca.

197
00:14:57,648 --> 00:15:01,735
Kanji ta, droid.

198
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:05,405
Yes, I am here, Your Worshipfulness.

199
00:15:05,489 --> 00:15:06,657
Yes?

200
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:14,748
[Speaking Huttese]

201
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:17,751
The illustrious Jabba
bids you welcome

202
00:15:17,835 --> 00:15:21,839
and will gladly pay you
the reward of 25,000.

203
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:24,049
I want 50,000. No less.

204
00:15:24,174 --> 00:15:26,760
50,000. No less.

205
00:15:26,844 --> 00:15:28,345
Wah! Aah!

206
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:29,763
Ohh!

207
00:15:29,847 --> 00:15:32,432
[Speaking Huttese]

208
00:15:39,439 --> 00:15:41,483
What-What did I say?

209
00:15:41,608 --> 00:15:45,779
[Speaking Huttese]

210
00:15:45,904 --> 00:15:50,492
The mighty Jabba
asks why he must pay 50,000.

211
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:53,245
[Speaking Ubese]

212
00:15:53,370 --> 00:15:57,499
Because he’s holding a thermal detonator!

213
00:15:57,624 --> 00:15:58,375
Oh!

214
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,418
Aah!

215
00:15:59,543 --> 00:16:01,587
Rrrrrr!

216
00:16:01,712 --> 00:16:04,131
Ho ho ho ho ho ho!

217
00:16:04,214 --> 00:16:08,135
Ah ha ha ha ha!

218
00:16:08,218 --> 00:16:16,476
This bounty hunter is my kind of scum,
fearless and inventive.

219
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:25,444
[Speaking Huttese]

220
00:16:25,527 --> 00:16:28,655
Jabba offers the sum of 35...

221
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:30,908
and I do suggest you take it.

222
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,077
[Speaking Ubese]

223
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:38,248
He agrees!

224
00:16:39,374 --> 00:16:41,502
Arrrr!

225
00:16:41,585 --> 00:16:43,629
Grrr!

226
00:16:43,754 --> 00:16:45,506
[Playing Festive Tune]

227
00:16:46,632 --> 00:16:47,549
Ahh!

228
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:49,676
[Speaking Huttese]

229
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:53,263
[Speaking Ubese]

230
00:16:55,849 --> 00:16:58,185
Rrr!

231
00:16:58,268 --> 00:16:59,394
Arrrr!

232
00:17:08,278 --> 00:17:10,405
Arrrrr!

233
00:17:10,489 --> 00:17:13,575
Grrrr!

234
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,370
Rrrr!

235
00:17:16,453 --> 00:17:18,956
Grr!

236
00:17:19,206 --> 00:17:20,749
Rrrrr.

237
00:17:30,759 --> 00:17:31,885
[Burp]

238
00:17:47,943 --> 00:17:49,528
[Clink Clink]

239
00:18:29,526 --> 00:18:31,028
[Thud]

240
00:19:27,626 --> 00:19:31,380
Just relax for a moment.

241
00:19:31,505 --> 00:19:34,007
You’re free of the carbonite.

242
00:19:34,091 --> 00:19:38,053
Shh. You have hibernation sickness.

243
00:19:38,178 --> 00:19:39,847
I can’t see.

244
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:43,600
Your eyesight will return in time.

245
00:19:43,684 --> 00:19:45,352
Where am I?

246
00:19:45,435 --> 00:19:47,104
Jabba’s palace.

247
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:50,899
Who are you?

248
00:19:56,446 --> 00:19:58,073
Someone who loves you.

249
00:19:58,198 --> 00:19:59,408
Leia.

250
00:20:01,994 --> 00:20:04,913
I got to get you out of here.

251
00:20:05,038 --> 00:20:07,374
Ho ho ho ho ho!

252
00:20:07,457 --> 00:20:08,375
What’s that?

253
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:11,003
Ho ho ho ho ho!

254
00:20:11,086 --> 00:20:13,005
I know that laugh.

255
00:20:13,088 --> 00:20:18,969
[Speaking Huttese]

256
00:20:19,052 --> 00:20:20,596
Hey, Jabba...

257
00:20:20,679 --> 00:20:22,514
Look, Jabba,

258
00:20:22,639 --> 00:20:24,516
I was just on my way to pay you back,

259
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,893
and I got a little sidetracked.

260
00:20:25,976 --> 00:20:27,227
It’s not my fault.

261
00:20:27,352 --> 00:20:31,064
It’s too late for that, Solo.

262
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:35,903
You may have been a good smuggler...

263
00:20:36,028 --> 00:20:39,489
but now you’re Bantha fodder.

264
00:20:39,615 --> 00:20:41,575
Ah ha ha ha!

265
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,368
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

266
00:20:43,493 --> 00:20:45,120
Look-

267
00:20:46,496 --> 00:20:48,457
Take him away.

268
00:20:48,582 --> 00:20:50,083
Jabba, I’ll pay you triple.

269
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,877
You’re throwing away a fortune!

270
00:20:52,002 --> 00:20:53,837
Don’t be a fool!

271
00:20:53,921 --> 00:20:55,756
[Jabba Speaking Huttese]

272
00:20:55,881 --> 00:20:58,050
Bring her to me.

273
00:21:01,803 --> 00:21:03,972
We have powerful friends.

274
00:21:04,056 --> 00:21:06,600
You’re going to regret this.

275
00:21:08,519 --> 00:21:10,270
I’m sure.

276
00:21:10,395 --> 00:21:12,606
[Slurp]

277
00:21:12,689 --> 00:21:14,191
Ugh!

278
00:21:14,441 --> 00:21:16,151
Oh, I can’t bear to watch.

279
00:21:16,276 --> 00:21:19,196
Oh! Ah ha ha ha!

280
00:21:26,703 --> 00:21:29,706
Arrrrg.

281
00:21:29,831 --> 00:21:32,125
Chewie?

282
00:21:32,209 --> 00:21:33,210
Arrrr!

283
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:34,711
Chewie, is that you?

284
00:21:34,837 --> 00:21:35,879
Rarrr!

285
00:21:35,963 --> 00:21:37,798
Ch-Chewie!

286
00:21:37,923 --> 00:21:40,509
I can’t see, pal.

287
00:21:40,634 --> 00:21:42,135
What’s going on?

288
00:21:42,219 --> 00:21:44,429
Ar grr arr.

289
00:21:44,555 --> 00:21:45,973
Luke? Luke’s crazy.

290
00:21:46,056 --> 00:21:51,144
He can’t even take care of himself,
much less rescue anybody.

291
00:21:51,228 --> 00:21:53,063
Arrr rarrr.

292
00:21:53,188 --> 00:21:54,606
A Jedi knight?

293
00:21:54,690 --> 00:21:56,942
I’m out of it for a little while,

294
00:21:57,025 --> 00:21:59,528
everybody gets delusions of grandeur.

295
00:21:59,611 --> 00:22:00,946
Arrra!

296
00:22:03,156 --> 00:22:05,075
I’m all right, pal.

297
00:22:05,158 --> 00:22:06,660
Arrrrrrr.

298
00:22:06,743 --> 00:22:08,120
I’m all right.

299
00:22:29,558 --> 00:22:31,977
Grrr!

300
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:33,687
Grrr!

301
00:22:35,898 --> 00:22:38,025
Arg.

302
00:22:58,086 --> 00:23:00,380
Yo macka chipowan Skywalker.

303
00:23:00,506 --> 00:23:01,882
Jabba mo botowa tu.

304
00:23:01,965 --> 00:23:05,052
I must speak with Jabba.

305
00:23:05,135 --> 00:23:07,304
Es tosit.

306
00:23:07,554 --> 00:23:09,723
Jabba no tusen di hunka bi.

307
00:23:09,806 --> 00:23:11,642
No bargain.

308
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:15,103
You will take me to Jabba now.

309
00:23:15,187 --> 00:23:17,981
Ataka bu Jabba now.

310
00:23:18,065 --> 00:23:20,609
You serve your master well.

311
00:23:20,692 --> 00:23:22,319
Ay sota vanlocha.

312
00:23:22,569 --> 00:23:24,321
And you will be rewarded.

313
00:23:24,613 --> 00:23:27,157
A chunoh ayo ahtot.

314
00:23:33,205 --> 00:23:36,625
At last! Master Luke’s come to rescue me.

315
00:23:36,708 --> 00:23:37,709
Master.

316
00:23:37,793 --> 00:23:39,127
Oohh!

317
00:23:39,211 --> 00:23:43,215
Gabba nopez Luke Skywalker,
Jedi knight.

318
00:23:43,298 --> 00:23:47,719
I told you not to admit him.

319
00:23:47,803 --> 00:23:49,638
I must be allowed to speak.

320
00:23:49,721 --> 00:23:52,349
He must be allowed to speak.

321
00:23:53,183 --> 00:23:56,186
You weak-minded fool!

322
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:58,105
Eee! Ah!

323
00:23:58,188 --> 00:24:02,693
He’s using an old Jedi mind trick.

324
00:24:02,776 --> 00:24:06,154
You will bring Captain Solo
and the Wookiee to me.

325
00:24:06,238 --> 00:24:10,200
Ho ho ho ho ho!

326
00:24:12,119 --> 00:24:17,291
Your mind powers will not work on me, boy.

327
00:24:17,374 --> 00:24:22,796
Nevertheless,
I’m taking Captain Solo and his friends.

328
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:26,008
You can either profit by this
or be destroyed.

329
00:24:26,091 --> 00:24:29,803
It’s your choice, but I warn you
not to underestimate my powers.

330
00:24:29,887 --> 00:24:31,930
Ooahh.

331
00:24:32,014 --> 00:24:34,099
Master Luke, you’re standing on-

332
00:24:34,183 --> 00:24:38,896
There will be no bargain, young Jedi.

333
00:24:40,022 --> 00:24:43,692
I shall enjoy watching you die.

334
00:24:46,236 --> 00:24:47,696
Grr!

335
00:24:50,991 --> 00:24:52,409
Ho ho ho!

336
00:25:03,253 --> 00:25:05,130
Tibi Jedi!

337
00:25:05,214 --> 00:25:07,257
Tibi Jedi!

338
00:25:07,424 --> 00:25:09,009
[Creaking]

339
00:25:14,723 --> 00:25:17,267
Oh, no! The rancor!

340
00:25:28,362 --> 00:25:31,031
Grr!

341
00:25:31,114 --> 00:25:34,993
[Squealing]

342
00:25:42,084 --> 00:25:44,211
[Squealing]

343
00:25:44,294 --> 00:25:46,463
Grr!

344
00:25:46,713 --> 00:25:47,923
[Squealing]

345
00:25:50,259 --> 00:25:51,301
[Crunch]

346
00:26:02,938 --> 00:26:05,148
Ha ha ha!

347
00:26:05,232 --> 00:26:07,484
Grr!

348
00:26:19,204 --> 00:26:20,414
Grrr!

349
00:26:20,497 --> 00:26:21,832
Oh!

350
00:26:24,084 --> 00:26:25,502
Whoo-hoo!

351
00:26:51,361 --> 00:26:53,989
Grr!

352
00:27:20,182 --> 00:27:22,267
Ya! Ha!

353
00:27:22,351 --> 00:27:24,228
Ah ha ha!

354
00:27:24,311 --> 00:27:26,563
Grr!

355
00:27:37,950 --> 00:27:39,409
[Crunch]

356
00:27:41,453 --> 00:27:43,497
[Speaking Huttese]

357
00:27:43,580 --> 00:27:45,999
[Whining]

358
00:27:49,086 --> 00:27:50,921
[Speaking Huttese]

359
00:27:54,091 --> 00:27:56,343
[Speaking Huttese]

360
00:28:04,476 --> 00:28:08,230
Bring me Solo and the Wookiee.

361
00:28:08,313 --> 00:28:12,526
They will all suffer for this outrage.

362
00:28:27,416 --> 00:28:28,417
Han!

363
00:28:28,500 --> 00:28:30,878
Luke!

364
00:28:30,961 --> 00:28:32,921
Are you all right?

365
00:28:33,005 --> 00:28:34,339
Fine. Together again, huh?

366
00:28:34,423 --> 00:28:35,924
Wouldn’t miss it.

367
00:28:36,008 --> 00:28:37,467
How are we doing?

368
00:28:37,551 --> 00:28:39,052
Same as always.

369
00:28:39,136 --> 00:28:40,512
That bad, huh?

370
00:28:40,596 --> 00:28:41,555
Where’s Leia?

371
00:28:41,638 --> 00:28:44,141
I’m here.

372
00:28:44,224 --> 00:28:46,351
[Speaking Huttese]

373
00:28:46,435 --> 00:28:48,478
[C-3PO]
Oh, dear.

374
00:28:48,562 --> 00:28:52,232
His High Exaltedness,
the great Jabba the Hutt,

375
00:28:52,316 --> 00:28:55,360
has decreed that you are to
be terminated immediately.

376
00:28:55,444 --> 00:28:57,196
Good. I hate long waits.

377
00:28:57,279 --> 00:28:59,406
Oh ah ha ha ha ha!

378
00:28:59,489 --> 00:29:04,578
You will therefore be taken to the Dune Sea
and cast into the Pit of Carkoon,

379
00:29:04,661 --> 00:29:06,914
the nesting place
of the all-powerful Sarlacc.

380
00:29:06,997 --> 00:29:08,373
Doesn’t sound so bad.

381
00:29:08,457 --> 00:29:12,377
In his belly, you will find
a new definition of pain and suffering,

382
00:29:12,461 --> 00:29:15,547
as you are slowly digested over 1,000 years.

383
00:29:15,631 --> 00:29:17,049
Aaarrrr!

384
00:29:17,132 --> 00:29:19,426
On second thought, let’s pass on that.

385
00:29:19,510 --> 00:29:21,053
You should have bargained.

386
00:29:21,136 --> 00:29:24,515
[Speaking Huttese]

387
00:29:24,598 --> 00:29:27,267
That’s the last mistake you’ll ever make.

388
00:29:27,351 --> 00:29:29,394
Ho ho ho ho ho!

389
00:29:29,478 --> 00:29:32,147
Ah ha ha ha ha!

390
00:29:55,379 --> 00:29:57,506
[Band Playing Festive Tune]

391
00:30:18,193 --> 00:30:20,487
I think my eyes are getting better.

392
00:30:20,571 --> 00:30:24,533
Instead of a big dark blur,
I see a big light blur.

393
00:30:24,616 --> 00:30:26,034
There’s nothing to see.

394
00:30:26,118 --> 00:30:27,536
I used to live here, you know.

395
00:30:27,619 --> 00:30:29,496
You’re going to die here, you know.

396
00:30:29,580 --> 00:30:30,747
Convenient.

397
00:30:30,998 --> 00:30:33,250
Just stick close to Chewie and Lando.

398
00:30:33,333 --> 00:30:35,252
I’ve taken care of everything.

399
00:30:35,335 --> 00:30:37,754
Oh. Great.

400
00:30:38,046 --> 00:30:39,173
Aah!

401
00:30:39,256 --> 00:30:40,757
Ow!

402
00:30:42,050 --> 00:30:48,348
Soon you will learn to appreciate me.

403
00:30:49,141 --> 00:30:50,184
[Beep Whistle]

404
00:30:50,267 --> 00:30:51,518
I’m terribly sorry.

405
00:30:51,602 --> 00:30:54,021
R2, what are you doing here?

406
00:30:54,104 --> 00:30:55,147
[Bleep Beep]

407
00:30:55,230 --> 00:30:57,357
Well, I can see you’re serving drinks,
but this place is dangerous.

408
00:30:57,441 --> 00:31:00,777
They’re going to execute Master Luke
and, if we’re not careful, us, too.

409
00:31:01,028 --> 00:31:03,071
[Beep Beep]

410
00:31:03,155 --> 00:31:05,616
Hmmph! I wish I had your confidence.

411
00:31:13,081 --> 00:31:14,499
Grrrr!

412
00:31:23,675 --> 00:31:25,302
Arrr.

413
00:31:25,385 --> 00:31:28,096
[Speaking Huttese]

414
00:31:28,263 --> 00:31:31,225
[C-3PO]
Victims of the almighty Sarlacc,

415
00:31:31,308 --> 00:31:34,394
His Excellency hopes
that you will die honorably.

416
00:31:34,478 --> 00:31:38,440
But should any of you wish to beg for mercy,

417
00:31:38,524 --> 00:31:43,070
the great Jabba the Hutt
will now listen to your pleas.

418
00:31:43,153 --> 00:31:44,613
[Beep Beep Whistle]

419
00:31:44,696 --> 00:31:47,157
Tibi Jedi.

420
00:31:47,241 --> 00:31:56,083
3PO, you tell that slimy piece of worm-ridden filth
he’ll get no such pleasure from us! Right?

421
00:31:56,166 --> 00:31:57,292
Grr!

422
00:31:58,669 --> 00:32:00,420
Jabba...

423
00:32:00,504 --> 00:32:02,589
this is your last chance.

424
00:32:02,673 --> 00:32:04,758
Free us or die.

425
00:32:04,842 --> 00:32:07,135
Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

426
00:32:09,304 --> 00:32:12,182
Move him into position.

427
00:32:26,488 --> 00:32:28,699
[Beep Beep]

428
00:32:36,290 --> 00:32:38,542
Put him in.

429
00:32:59,229 --> 00:33:00,814
Aah!

430
00:33:00,898 --> 00:33:02,774
Grr!

431
00:33:02,858 --> 00:33:04,484
Easy, Chewie.

432
00:33:14,411 --> 00:33:15,787
Help!

433
00:33:22,586 --> 00:33:24,755
Chewie, you’re hit? Where is it?

434
00:33:29,927 --> 00:33:32,387
Han! Chewie!

435
00:33:32,471 --> 00:33:33,555
Lando!

436
00:33:41,688 --> 00:33:42,940
Boba Fett?

437
00:33:44,483 --> 00:33:46,485
Boba Fett? Where?

438
00:33:47,945 --> 00:33:50,405
Eeyaah!

439
00:33:50,489 --> 00:33:51,573
Uhh!

440
00:33:56,453 --> 00:33:57,955
[Burp]

441
00:34:19,601 --> 00:34:20,561
Lando, grab it!

442
00:34:20,644 --> 00:34:21,603
Lower it!

443
00:34:21,687 --> 00:34:23,272
I’m trying!

444
00:34:24,523 --> 00:34:25,691
Augghh!

445
00:34:34,908 --> 00:34:38,829
[Death Rattle]

446
00:34:45,335 --> 00:34:47,713
- Grab me, Chewie.
- I’m slipping!

447
00:35:00,434 --> 00:35:02,686
Grab it! Almost... You almost got it.

448
00:35:11,945 --> 00:35:13,447
Gently, now.

449
00:35:13,530 --> 00:35:15,574
All right. Easy, easy. Hold me, Chewie.

450
00:35:15,657 --> 00:35:17,868
Eeyaah!

451
00:35:17,951 --> 00:35:19,036
Chewie!

452
00:35:25,501 --> 00:35:27,920
Chewie, give me the gun.

453
00:35:28,003 --> 00:35:30,047
Don’t move, Lando.

454
00:35:30,339 --> 00:35:31,924
Wait! I thought you were blind!

455
00:35:32,007 --> 00:35:33,967
It’s all right! I can see a lot better!
Don’t move!

456
00:35:34,051 --> 00:35:35,761
A little higher! Just a little higher!

457
00:35:38,889 --> 00:35:40,891
Chewie, pull us up.

458
00:35:41,975 --> 00:35:43,644
Up, Chewie. Up.

459
00:35:45,479 --> 00:35:47,648
Come on. We gotta get out of here.

460
00:35:47,731 --> 00:35:49,566
Not my eyes! R2, help!

461
00:35:49,650 --> 00:35:51,652
Quickly, R2!

462
00:35:53,028 --> 00:35:54,071
Beast!

463
00:35:54,363 --> 00:35:56,073
Eh heh. Boo ba daba da!

464
00:35:58,867 --> 00:36:00,410
Get the gun!

465
00:36:01,537 --> 00:36:02,788
Point it at the deck!

466
00:36:08,377 --> 00:36:09,837
Point it at the deck!

467
00:36:13,632 --> 00:36:15,509
R2, where are we going?
I couldn’t possibly go-

468
00:36:15,592 --> 00:36:17,344
Aah!

469
00:36:17,427 --> 00:36:19,096
[Whistle]

470
00:36:20,639 --> 00:36:22,349
Come on!

471
00:36:29,982 --> 00:36:32,526
Let’s go. And don’t forget the droids.

472
00:36:32,609 --> 00:36:34,570
We’re on our way.

473
00:36:37,990 --> 00:36:41,952
[Beep Whistle Whistle]

474
00:36:43,996 --> 00:36:45,581
[Whistle]

475
00:37:12,858 --> 00:37:14,401
I’ll meet you back at the fleet.

476
00:37:14,484 --> 00:37:15,611
[Leia]
Hurry.

477
00:37:15,694 --> 00:37:17,154
The Alliance should be assembled by now.

478
00:37:17,446 --> 00:37:18,405
I will.

479
00:37:18,488 --> 00:37:19,781
[Han]
Hey, Luke, thanks.

480
00:37:19,865 --> 00:37:21,783
Thanks for coming after me.

481
00:37:21,867 --> 00:37:24,703
Now I owe you one.

482
00:37:24,786 --> 00:37:26,622
[Whistle Beep]

483
00:37:27,956 --> 00:37:31,752
That’s right, R2.
We’re going to the Dagobah system.

484
00:37:34,087 --> 00:37:36,423
[Whistle]

485
00:37:38,050 --> 00:37:40,427
I have a promise to keep...

486
00:37:40,511 --> 00:37:42,513
to an old friend.

487
00:38:32,688 --> 00:38:35,065
Rise, my friend.

488
00:38:41,822 --> 00:38:45,033
The Death Star will be completed on schedule.

489
00:38:45,117 --> 00:38:47,828
You’ve done well, Lord Vader.

490
00:38:47,911 --> 00:38:54,251
And now I sense you wish
to continue your search for young Skywalker.

491
00:38:56,712 --> 00:38:58,172
Yes, my master.

492
00:38:58,255 --> 00:39:01,175
Patience, my friend.

493
00:39:01,258 --> 00:39:04,761
In time, he will seek you out.

494
00:39:04,845 --> 00:39:09,183
And when he does,
you must bring him before me.

495
00:39:09,266 --> 00:39:11,643
He has grown strong.

496
00:39:11,727 --> 00:39:17,649
Only together can we turn him
to the dark side of the Force.

497
00:39:17,733 --> 00:39:19,776
As you wish.

498
00:39:19,860 --> 00:39:26,283
Everything is proceeding as I have foreseen.

499
00:39:26,533 --> 00:39:30,829
Ha ha ha ha!

500
00:39:36,084 --> 00:39:39,630
[Beep Whistle]

501
00:39:50,891 --> 00:39:53,894
That face you make...

502
00:39:53,977 --> 00:39:56,897
Look I so old to young eyes?

503
00:39:56,980 --> 00:39:59,107
No, of course not.

504
00:39:59,191 --> 00:40:01,151
I do.

505
00:40:05,239 --> 00:40:06,865
Yes, I do.

506
00:40:09,034 --> 00:40:11,703
Sick have I become.

507
00:40:11,787 --> 00:40:14,039
Old and weak.

508
00:40:16,917 --> 00:40:22,673
When 900 years old you reach,
look as good you will not, hmm?

509
00:40:22,756 --> 00:40:25,008
Heh heh heh.

510
00:40:28,804 --> 00:40:31,098
Soon will I rest.

511
00:40:31,181 --> 00:40:32,975
Yes.

512
00:40:33,058 --> 00:40:35,811
Forever sleep.

513
00:40:35,894 --> 00:40:38,105
Earned it I have.

514
00:40:38,188 --> 00:40:40,941
Master Yoda, you can’t die.

515
00:40:41,024 --> 00:40:46,905
Strong am I with the Force,
but not that strong.

516
00:40:49,366 --> 00:40:54,955
Twilight is upon me, and soon night must fall.

517
00:40:58,083 --> 00:41:00,794
That is the way of things...

518
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:05,132
the way of the Force.

519
00:41:06,925 --> 00:41:08,844
But I need your help.

520
00:41:08,927 --> 00:41:12,014
I’ve come back to complete the training.

521
00:41:12,097 --> 00:41:14,975
No more training do you require.

522
00:41:15,058 --> 00:41:18,395
Already know you that which you need.

523
00:41:20,772 --> 00:41:22,983
Then I am a Jedi.

524
00:41:23,066 --> 00:41:24,651
Oh!

525
00:41:24,735 --> 00:41:29,406
[Laughs, Coughs]

526
00:41:29,698 --> 00:41:31,658
Not yet.

527
00:41:31,742 --> 00:41:33,994
One thing remains-

528
00:41:34,077 --> 00:41:35,412
Vader.

529
00:41:35,704 --> 00:41:39,166
You must confront Vader.

530
00:41:39,249 --> 00:41:44,129
Then, only then, a Jedi will you be.

531
00:41:45,339 --> 00:41:47,925
And confront him you will.

532
00:41:51,970 --> 00:41:53,847
Master Yoda...

533
00:41:57,142 --> 00:42:00,103
is Darth Vader my father?

534
00:42:03,106 --> 00:42:05,442
Rest I need.

535
00:42:05,692 --> 00:42:07,027
Yes.

536
00:42:07,110 --> 00:42:08,445
Rest.

537
00:42:10,697 --> 00:42:12,449
Yoda, I must know.

538
00:42:16,954 --> 00:42:19,748
Your father he is.

539
00:42:24,962 --> 00:42:27,047
Told you, did he?

540
00:42:29,466 --> 00:42:31,468
Yes.

541
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:35,097
Unexpected this is.

542
00:42:37,224 --> 00:42:39,101
And unfortunate.

543
00:42:39,184 --> 00:42:42,813
Unfortunate that I know the truth?

544
00:42:42,896 --> 00:42:44,314
No.

545
00:42:47,067 --> 00:42:51,071
Unfortunate that you rushed to face him,

546
00:42:51,154 --> 00:42:54,825
that incomplete was your training,

547
00:42:54,908 --> 00:42:59,079
that not ready for the burden were you.

548
00:43:00,163 --> 00:43:02,916
I’m sorry.

549
00:43:02,999 --> 00:43:04,251
Remember...

550
00:43:04,334 --> 00:43:09,214
a Jedi’s strength flows from the Force.

551
00:43:13,510 --> 00:43:15,429
But beware-

552
00:43:15,512 --> 00:43:19,141
Anger, fear, aggression...

553
00:43:19,224 --> 00:43:22,269
the dark side are they.

554
00:43:22,352 --> 00:43:26,440
Once you start down the dark path,

555
00:43:26,523 --> 00:43:30,944
forever will it dominate your destiny.

556
00:43:32,988 --> 00:43:35,449
Luke...

557
00:43:35,532 --> 00:43:36,867
Luke...

558
00:43:36,950 --> 00:43:39,828
do not...

559
00:43:42,122 --> 00:43:47,920
do not underestimate
the powers of the emperor,

560
00:43:48,003 --> 00:43:51,965
or suffer your father’s fate you will.

561
00:43:54,259 --> 00:43:55,344
Luke...

562
00:43:55,427 --> 00:43:58,805
when gone am I,

563
00:43:58,889 --> 00:44:03,143
the last of the Jedi will you be.

564
00:44:03,227 --> 00:44:05,020
Luke...

565
00:44:06,563 --> 00:44:12,569
the Force runs strong in your family.

566
00:44:12,819 --> 00:44:17,074
Pass on what you have learned.

567
00:44:19,368 --> 00:44:20,452
Luke...

568
00:44:26,250 --> 00:44:29,294
there is...

569
00:44:29,378 --> 00:44:31,296
another...

570
00:44:33,257 --> 00:44:35,175
Sk...

571
00:44:35,259 --> 00:44:39,972
Sky...walker.

572
00:45:27,895 --> 00:45:29,229
[Beep Beep]

573
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:42,159
I can’t do it, R2.

574
00:45:42,242 --> 00:45:44,119
[Beep Whistle]

575
00:45:45,996 --> 00:45:48,415
I can’t go on alone.

576
00:45:48,498 --> 00:45:51,919
Yoda will always be with you.

577
00:45:52,002 --> 00:45:53,504
Obi-Wan.

578
00:46:01,178 --> 00:46:03,222
Why didn’t you tell me?

579
00:46:03,305 --> 00:46:06,934
You told me Vader
betrayed and murdered my father.

580
00:46:07,017 --> 00:46:12,314
Your father was seduced by
the dark side of the Force.

581
00:46:12,397 --> 00:46:16,944
He ceased to be Anakin Skywalker
and became Darth Vader.

582
00:46:17,027 --> 00:46:22,616
When that happened, the good man
who was your father was destroyed.

583
00:46:22,699 --> 00:46:25,327
So what I told you was true...

584
00:46:25,410 --> 00:46:27,246
from a certain point of view.

585
00:46:27,329 --> 00:46:29,706
A certain point of view?

586
00:46:29,998 --> 00:46:36,964
Luke, you’re going to find
that many of the truths we cling to
depend greatly on our own point of view.

587
00:46:37,047 --> 00:46:40,342
Anakin was a good friend.

588
00:46:40,425 --> 00:46:45,097
When I first knew him,
your father was already a great pilot,

589
00:46:45,180 --> 00:46:48,225
but I was amazed
how strongly the Force was with him.

590
00:46:48,308 --> 00:46:52,646
I took it upon myself to train him as a Jedi.

591
00:46:52,729 --> 00:46:57,067
I thought that I could instruct him
just as well as Yoda.

592
00:46:57,150 --> 00:46:58,485
I was wrong.

593
00:46:58,569 --> 00:47:01,321
There is still good in him.

594
00:47:01,405 --> 00:47:04,241
He’s more machine now than man,

595
00:47:04,324 --> 00:47:07,286
twisted and evil.

596
00:47:07,369 --> 00:47:09,746
I can’t do it, Ben.

597
00:47:10,038 --> 00:47:12,332
You cannot escape your destiny.

598
00:47:12,416 --> 00:47:15,627
You must face Darth Vader again.

599
00:47:15,711 --> 00:47:18,589
I can’t kill my own father.

600
00:47:21,300 --> 00:47:25,262
Then the emperor has already won.

601
00:47:25,345 --> 00:47:28,682
You were our only hope.

602
00:47:28,765 --> 00:47:31,351
Yoda spoke of another.

603
00:47:33,353 --> 00:47:36,315
The other he spoke of is your twin sister.

604
00:47:36,398 --> 00:47:38,775
But I have no sister.

605
00:47:39,067 --> 00:47:41,778
To protect you both from the emperor,

606
00:47:42,070 --> 00:47:45,365
you were hidden from your father
when you were born.

607
00:47:45,449 --> 00:47:48,243
The emperor knew, as I did,

608
00:47:48,327 --> 00:47:51,788
if Anakin were to have any offspring,

609
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:54,791
they would be a threat to him.

610
00:47:55,083 --> 00:48:00,380
That is the reason
why your sister remains safely anonymous.

611
00:48:00,464 --> 00:48:02,216
Leia!

612
00:48:02,299 --> 00:48:04,051
Leia’s my sister.

613
00:48:04,134 --> 00:48:07,471
Your insight serves you well.

614
00:48:07,554 --> 00:48:11,183
Bury your feelings deep down, Luke.

615
00:48:11,266 --> 00:48:16,813
They do you credit,
but they could be made to serve the emperor.

616
00:48:38,710 --> 00:48:41,296
Well, look at you- a general, huh?

617
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:45,259
Someone must have told them about
my little maneuver at the Battle of Tanaab.

618
00:48:45,342 --> 00:48:48,095
Well, don’t look at me, pal.
I just said you were a fair pilot.

619
00:48:48,178 --> 00:48:51,306
I didn’t know they were looking for somebody
to lead this crazy attack.

620
00:48:51,390 --> 00:48:53,517
I’m surprised they didn’t ask you to do it.

621
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:56,728
Who says they didn’t? But I ain’t crazy.

622
00:48:56,812 --> 00:48:59,439
You’re the respectable one, remember?

623
00:48:59,523 --> 00:49:02,192
[Chimes]

624
00:49:05,821 --> 00:49:09,575
The emperor’s made a critical error,
and the time for our attack has come.

625
00:49:09,658 --> 00:49:16,498
The data brought to us by the Bothan spies
pinpoint the exact location
of the emperor’s new battle station.

626
00:49:16,582 --> 00:49:20,752
We also know that the weapon systems
of this Death Star are not yet operational.

627
00:49:20,836 --> 00:49:23,755
With the imperial fleet
spread throughout the galaxy,

628
00:49:23,839 --> 00:49:25,465
in a vain effort to engage us,

629
00:49:25,549 --> 00:49:27,509
it is relatively unprotected.

630
00:49:27,593 --> 00:49:30,262
But most important of all,

631
00:49:30,345 --> 00:49:37,394
we’ve learned that the emperor himself
is personally overseeing the final stages
of the construction of this Death Star.

632
00:49:37,477 --> 00:49:43,650
Many Bothans died to
bring us this information.

633
00:49:43,734 --> 00:49:45,194
Admiral Ackbar, please.

634
00:49:45,277 --> 00:49:51,783
You can see here the Death Star
orbiting the forest moon of Endor.

635
00:49:51,867 --> 00:49:56,705
Although the weapon systems
on this Death Star are not yet operational,

636
00:49:56,788 --> 00:50:01,168
the Death Star does have
a strong defense mechanism.

637
00:50:01,251 --> 00:50:08,467
It is protected by an energy shield which is generated
from the nearby forest moon of Endor.

638
00:50:11,803 --> 00:50:17,726
The shield must be deactivated
if any attack is to be attempted.

639
00:50:17,809 --> 00:50:23,190
Once the shield is down,
our cruisers will create a perimeter

640
00:50:23,273 --> 00:50:30,364
while the fighters fly into the superstructure
and attempt to knock out the main reactor.

641
00:50:30,447 --> 00:50:35,202
General Calrissian has volunteered
to lead the fighter attack.

642
00:50:35,285 --> 00:50:36,578
Good luck.

643
00:50:38,247 --> 00:50:40,207
You’re going to need it.

644
00:50:40,290 --> 00:50:42,334
General Madine.

645
00:50:42,417 --> 00:50:45,879
We have stolen a small imperial shuttle.

646
00:50:45,963 --> 00:50:50,342
Disguised as a cargo ship
and using a secret imperial code,

647
00:50:50,425 --> 00:50:55,264
a strike team will land on the moon
and deactivate the shield generator.

648
00:50:55,347 --> 00:50:56,557
Sounds dangerous.

649
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:58,892
I wonder who they found
to pull that off.

650
00:50:58,976 --> 00:51:02,229
General Solo,
is your strike team assembled?

651
00:51:02,312 --> 00:51:03,605
Uh, my team’s ready.

652
00:51:03,689 --> 00:51:06,233
I don’t have a command crew
for the shuttle.

653
00:51:06,316 --> 00:51:07,276
Arrr!

654
00:51:07,359 --> 00:51:09,444
It’s going to be rough, pal.
I didn’t wanna speak for you.

655
00:51:09,528 --> 00:51:11,613
Arr!

656
00:51:11,697 --> 00:51:12,739
That’s one.

657
00:51:12,823 --> 00:51:15,784
General... count me in.

658
00:51:15,868 --> 00:51:17,828
I’m with you, too.

659
00:51:22,958 --> 00:51:24,418
What is it?

660
00:51:24,501 --> 00:51:26,628
Ask me again sometime.

661
00:51:26,712 --> 00:51:27,671
Luke.

662
00:51:27,754 --> 00:51:30,340
Hi, Han, Chewie.

663
00:51:30,424 --> 00:51:31,633
[Whistle]

664
00:51:31,717 --> 00:51:34,344
"Exciting" is hardly the word I would choose.

665
00:51:48,901 --> 00:51:52,446
Look, I want you to take her.

666
00:51:52,529 --> 00:51:54,281
I mean it. Take her.

667
00:51:54,364 --> 00:51:55,824
You need all the help you can get.

668
00:51:55,908 --> 00:51:57,701
She’s the fastest ship in the fleet.

669
00:51:57,784 --> 00:51:59,578
All right, old buddy.

670
00:51:59,661 --> 00:52:02,372
I know what she means to you.

671
00:52:02,456 --> 00:52:03,957
I’ll take good care of her.

672
00:52:04,041 --> 00:52:06,668
She won’t get a scratch.

673
00:52:06,752 --> 00:52:08,295
All right?

674
00:52:08,378 --> 00:52:09,755
Right.

675
00:52:16,053 --> 00:52:17,971
I got your promise.

676
00:52:18,055 --> 00:52:19,723
Not a scratch.

677
00:52:19,806 --> 00:52:22,017
Would you get going, you pirate?

678
00:52:23,727 --> 00:52:24,895
Good luck.

679
00:52:24,978 --> 00:52:26,396
You, too.

680
00:52:35,697 --> 00:52:36,615
Got her warmed?

681
00:52:36,698 --> 00:52:37,658
She’s coming up.

682
00:52:37,741 --> 00:52:39,326
Arr!

683
00:52:39,409 --> 00:52:44,081
Yeah, well, I don’t think the Empire had Wookiees
in mind when they designed her, Chewie.

684
00:52:53,924 --> 00:52:56,009
Hey, you awake?

685
00:52:56,093 --> 00:53:01,431
Yeah. I just got a funny feeling,
like I’m not gonna see her again.

686
00:53:01,515 --> 00:53:03,809
Come on, General, let’s move.

687
00:53:03,892 --> 00:53:07,771
Right. Chewie, let’s see
what this piece of junk can do.

688
00:53:07,855 --> 00:53:09,356
Ready, everybody?

689
00:53:09,439 --> 00:53:10,983
All set.

690
00:53:11,066 --> 00:53:12,568
[Whistle]

691
00:53:12,651 --> 00:53:14,570
Here we go again.

692
00:53:25,497 --> 00:53:27,374
All right, hang on.

693
00:53:42,139 --> 00:53:45,767
What is thy bidding, my master?

694
00:53:45,851 --> 00:53:50,689
Send the fleet to the far side of Endor.

695
00:53:53,483 --> 00:53:57,988
There it will stay until called for.

696
00:53:59,615 --> 00:54:03,160
What of the reports of the rebel fleet
massing near Sullust?

697
00:54:03,452 --> 00:54:05,746
It is of no concern.

698
00:54:05,829 --> 00:54:10,542
Soon the rebellion will be crushed
and young Skywalker will be one of us.

699
00:54:10,626 --> 00:54:12,753
Your work here is finished, my friend.

700
00:54:12,836 --> 00:54:15,547
Go out to the command ship
and await my orders.

701
00:54:15,631 --> 00:54:17,007
Yes, my master.

702
00:54:33,190 --> 00:54:36,443
If they don’t go for this, we’re gonna
have to get out of here pretty quick, Chewie.

703
00:54:36,527 --> 00:54:37,945
Arrrr!

704
00:54:38,028 --> 00:54:39,947
[Radio]
We have you on our screen now.

705
00:54:40,030 --> 00:54:42,574
Please identify.

706
00:54:42,658 --> 00:54:46,787
Shuttle Tydirium requesting deactivation
of the deflector shield.

707
00:54:52,209 --> 00:54:56,463
Shuttle Tydirium, transmit
the clearance code for shield passage.

708
00:54:56,547 --> 00:54:59,132
Transmission commencing.

709
00:54:59,216 --> 00:55:02,219
Now we find out if that code is worth
the price we paid.

710
00:55:02,511 --> 00:55:05,222
It’ll work. It’ll work.

711
00:55:06,932 --> 00:55:09,101
Vader’s on that ship.

712
00:55:09,184 --> 00:55:13,564
Now, don’t get jittery, Luke.
There are a lot of command ships.

713
00:55:13,647 --> 00:55:15,566
Keep your distance, though, Chewie,

714
00:55:15,649 --> 00:55:18,068
but don’t look like you’re trying
to keep your distance.

715
00:55:18,151 --> 00:55:19,570
Arrrr?!

716
00:55:19,653 --> 00:55:22,239
I don’t know. Fly casual.

717
00:55:26,535 --> 00:55:28,954
Where is that shuttle going?

718
00:55:29,037 --> 00:55:33,876
Shuttle Tydirium,
what is your cargo and destination?

719
00:55:33,959 --> 00:55:36,128
Parts and technical crew for the forest moon.

720
00:55:38,255 --> 00:55:41,008
Do they have a code clearance?

721
00:55:41,091 --> 00:55:43,177
It’s an older code, sir, but it checks out.

722
00:55:43,260 --> 00:55:45,095
I was about to clear them.

723
00:55:49,183 --> 00:55:53,896
I’m endangering the mission.
I shouldn’t have come.

724
00:55:53,979 --> 00:55:55,772
It’s your imagination, kid.

725
00:55:55,856 --> 00:55:58,609
Let’s keep a little optimism here.

726
00:56:05,949 --> 00:56:08,076
Shall I hold them?

727
00:56:08,160 --> 00:56:09,953
No.

728
00:56:10,037 --> 00:56:11,538
Leave them to me.

729
00:56:11,622 --> 00:56:14,583
I will deal with them myself.

730
00:56:14,666 --> 00:56:17,711
As you wish, my lord. Carry on.

731
00:56:18,962 --> 00:56:21,882
They’re not going for it, Chewie.

732
00:56:25,719 --> 00:56:27,179
Shuttle Tydirium,

733
00:56:27,262 --> 00:56:28,972
deactivation of the shield
will commence immediately.

734
00:56:29,056 --> 00:56:30,307
Follow your present course.

735
00:56:30,557 --> 00:56:34,102
O.K. I told you it was going to work.

736
00:56:34,186 --> 00:56:36,146
No problem.

737
00:57:09,596 --> 00:57:11,682
Oh, I told you it was dangerous here!

738
00:57:26,989 --> 00:57:28,740
Should we try and go around?

739
00:57:28,824 --> 00:57:30,617
It’ll take time.

740
00:57:30,701 --> 00:57:33,662
This whole party will be
for nothing if they see us.

741
00:57:33,745 --> 00:57:35,372
Arr!

742
00:57:35,622 --> 00:57:38,792
Chewie and I will take care of this.
You stay here.

743
00:57:38,876 --> 00:57:41,628
Quietly. There might be more of them out there.

744
00:57:41,712 --> 00:57:44,381
Hey, it’s me.

745
00:58:06,737 --> 00:58:07,738
[Snap]

746
00:58:10,032 --> 00:58:12,034
Go for help! Go!

747
00:58:12,117 --> 00:58:13,744
Great. Come on!

748
00:58:29,092 --> 00:58:32,095
Over there! Two more of them.

749
00:58:32,179 --> 00:58:34,431
I see them. Wait, Leia!

750
00:58:38,101 --> 00:58:39,102
Hey, wait!

751
00:58:46,109 --> 00:58:49,279
Quick. Jam their comlink!
Center switch!

752
00:59:00,207 --> 00:59:01,917
Move closer!

753
00:59:04,253 --> 00:59:06,171
Get alongside that one!

754
00:59:16,932 --> 00:59:17,933
Oh!

755
00:59:47,171 --> 00:59:50,465
Keep on that one! I’ll take these two!

756
01:00:43,894 --> 01:00:44,895
Aah!

757
01:00:48,148 --> 01:00:49,149
Aah!

758
01:01:57,384 --> 01:02:02,055
[Whistle Beep Beep]

759
01:02:02,139 --> 01:02:05,058
General Solo, somebody’s coming.

760
01:02:05,142 --> 01:02:06,643
Urrr!

761
01:02:06,935 --> 01:02:08,187
Oh!

762
01:02:15,485 --> 01:02:17,070
Luke!

763
01:02:17,154 --> 01:02:18,155
Arrr!

764
01:02:18,238 --> 01:02:19,406
Where’s Leia?

765
01:02:19,489 --> 01:02:21,408
She didn’t come back?

766
01:02:21,491 --> 01:02:22,659
I thought she was with you.

767
01:02:22,951 --> 01:02:25,370
We got separated. We better go look for her.

768
01:02:25,454 --> 01:02:26,955
Take the squad ahead.

769
01:02:27,039 --> 01:02:29,249
We’ll meet at the shield generator at 0300.

770
01:02:29,333 --> 01:02:31,919
Come on, R2,
we’ll need your scanners.

771
01:02:32,002 --> 01:02:33,545
Don’t worry, Master Luke.

772
01:02:33,629 --> 01:02:36,548
We know what to do.

773
01:02:36,632 --> 01:02:39,635
And you said it was pretty here.

774
01:02:55,526 --> 01:02:57,110
Eek.

775
01:02:59,404 --> 01:03:00,948
Eek!

776
01:03:01,031 --> 01:03:02,950
Cut it out!

777
01:03:03,033 --> 01:03:04,243
Grrrrr.

778
01:03:06,370 --> 01:03:08,163
Rrrr.

779
01:03:10,415 --> 01:03:12,543
[Speaking Ewokese]

780
01:03:15,379 --> 01:03:18,006
Arrr. Arrr.

781
01:03:19,633 --> 01:03:22,970
I’m not going to hurt you.

782
01:03:23,053 --> 01:03:24,304
Oh.

783
01:03:24,388 --> 01:03:27,307
[Speaking Ewokese]

784
01:03:29,351 --> 01:03:32,646
Well, looks like I’m stuck here.

785
01:03:32,729 --> 01:03:36,733
Trouble is, I don’t know where here is.

786
01:03:37,025 --> 01:03:39,403
Maybe you can help me.

787
01:03:41,113 --> 01:03:42,739
Come on. Sit down.

788
01:03:42,990 --> 01:03:44,658
Grrrrr.

789
01:03:44,741 --> 01:03:46,994
I promise I won’t hurt you.
Now come here.

790
01:03:47,077 --> 01:03:48,495
Grrrrr!

791
01:03:48,579 --> 01:03:51,206
All right. You want something to eat?

792
01:03:53,083 --> 01:03:56,211
[Speaking Ewokese]

793
01:03:57,754 --> 01:03:59,590
That’s right.

794
01:04:03,719 --> 01:04:05,012
Come on.
[Speaking Ewokese]

795
01:04:05,095 --> 01:04:06,054
Hmm?

796
01:04:06,138 --> 01:04:09,183
[Sniff Sniff]

797
01:04:09,266 --> 01:04:11,185
[Speaking Ewokese]

798
01:04:17,149 --> 01:04:18,609
[Speaking Ewokese]

799
01:04:19,776 --> 01:04:21,528
Ya! Yee!

800
01:04:21,612 --> 01:04:25,073
[Speaking Ewokese]

801
01:04:25,157 --> 01:04:27,534
Look. It’s a hat.

802
01:04:27,618 --> 01:04:30,621
It’s not going to hurt you. Look.

803
01:04:30,704 --> 01:04:32,581
Arrr.

804
01:04:32,664 --> 01:04:35,209
[Speaking Ewokese]

805
01:04:35,292 --> 01:04:38,629
You’re a jittery little thing, aren’t you?

806
01:04:40,255 --> 01:04:42,549
Ooooh!

807
01:04:42,633 --> 01:04:44,051
[Sniff Sniff]

808
01:04:44,134 --> 01:04:45,511
What is it?

809
01:04:45,594 --> 01:04:47,137
[Speaking Ewokese]

810
01:04:53,519 --> 01:04:56,480
[Sniff Sniff Sniff]

811
01:04:59,107 --> 01:05:01,527
[Speaking Ewokese]

812
01:05:02,819 --> 01:05:03,570
[Zap]

813
01:05:03,654 --> 01:05:05,072
Oh!

814
01:05:05,155 --> 01:05:07,699
[Speaking Ewokese]

815
01:05:13,789 --> 01:05:17,543
[Speaking Ewokese]

816
01:05:24,675 --> 01:05:26,510
Freeze!

817
01:05:26,593 --> 01:05:28,762
Come on, get up!

818
01:05:28,846 --> 01:05:30,389
Grrrrr!

819
01:05:31,557 --> 01:05:34,726
Go get your ride. Take her back to base.

820
01:05:34,810 --> 01:05:36,311
Yes, sir.

821
01:05:39,648 --> 01:05:40,691
Rrrooh!

822
01:05:40,774 --> 01:05:42,109
What the-

823
01:05:42,192 --> 01:05:43,485
Ya!

824
01:05:55,372 --> 01:05:58,876
[Speaking Ewokese]

825
01:05:59,168 --> 01:06:02,462
Come on. Let’s get out of here.

826
01:06:08,677 --> 01:06:13,432
[Speaking Ewokese]

827
01:06:42,920 --> 01:06:47,508
I told you to remain on the command ship.

828
01:06:47,591 --> 01:06:54,598
A small rebel force has penetrated the shield
and landed on Endor.

829
01:06:54,681 --> 01:06:57,184
Yes, I know.

830
01:06:57,267 --> 01:07:01,230
My son is with them.

831
01:07:01,313 --> 01:07:03,190
Are you sure?

832
01:07:03,273 --> 01:07:06,443
I have felt him, my master.

833
01:07:07,694 --> 01:07:11,281
Strange that I have not.

834
01:07:11,365 --> 01:07:17,204
I wonder if your feelings
on this matter are clear, Lord Vader.

835
01:07:17,287 --> 01:07:19,957
They are clear, my master.

836
01:07:20,207 --> 01:07:24,419
Then you must go to the sanctuary moon
and wait for him.

837
01:07:24,503 --> 01:07:27,548
He will come to me?

838
01:07:27,631 --> 01:07:31,510
I have foreseen it.

839
01:07:31,593 --> 01:07:35,681
His compassion for you will be his undoing.

840
01:07:35,764 --> 01:07:40,394
He will come to you,
and then you will bring him before me.

841
01:07:40,477 --> 01:07:42,688
As you wish.

842
01:07:54,700 --> 01:07:56,827
Luke! Luke!

843
01:08:02,999 --> 01:08:05,002
Oh, Master Luke.

844
01:08:07,713 --> 01:08:09,298
Arrrrr.

845
01:08:09,381 --> 01:08:11,758
There’s two more
wrecked speeders back there.

846
01:08:11,842 --> 01:08:14,261
And I found this.

847
01:08:14,344 --> 01:08:20,934
I’m afraid that R2’s sensors
can find no trace of Princess Leia.

848
01:08:21,018 --> 01:08:24,021
I hope she’s all right.

849
01:08:26,356 --> 01:08:27,357
Arrrrr!

850
01:08:27,441 --> 01:08:28,567
Arrrrr!

851
01:08:28,650 --> 01:08:30,277
What, Chewie?

852
01:08:30,360 --> 01:08:32,029
Arrrrr!

853
01:08:32,279 --> 01:08:34,656
What, Chewie?

854
01:08:34,740 --> 01:08:36,783
Arrrrrrrr.

855
01:08:36,867 --> 01:08:38,660
Arrrr.

856
01:08:38,744 --> 01:08:40,370
Arrr.

857
01:08:47,628 --> 01:08:48,921
I don’t get it.

858
01:08:49,004 --> 01:08:51,673
It’s just a dead animal, Chewie.

859
01:08:51,757 --> 01:08:53,050
Chewie, wait!

860
01:08:53,342 --> 01:08:54,468
Don’t!

861
01:08:54,551 --> 01:08:57,387
Aah!

862
01:08:58,889 --> 01:09:00,557
Nice work.

863
01:09:00,641 --> 01:09:01,975
Arrrrr!

864
01:09:02,059 --> 01:09:03,393
Great, Chewie.

865
01:09:03,477 --> 01:09:06,313
Great. Always thinking with your stomach.

866
01:09:06,396 --> 01:09:09,983
Take it easy. Let’s just figure a way
to get out of this thing.

867
01:09:10,067 --> 01:09:11,818
Han, can you reach my lightsaber?

868
01:09:11,902 --> 01:09:14,446
Yeah. Sure.

869
01:09:14,530 --> 01:09:15,781
[Whistle Beep Beep]

870
01:09:18,659 --> 01:09:22,663
R2, I’m not sure that’s such a good idea.

871
01:09:22,746 --> 01:09:24,706
It’s a very long drop!

872
01:09:37,761 --> 01:09:39,721
Ah.

873
01:09:39,805 --> 01:09:43,100
[Speaking Ewokese]

874
01:09:43,392 --> 01:09:45,853
[Speaking Ewokese]

875
01:09:59,116 --> 01:10:01,785
[Speaking Ewokese]

876
01:10:01,869 --> 01:10:03,120
What-

877
01:10:07,457 --> 01:10:10,544
Hey! Point that thing someplace else.

878
01:10:10,627 --> 01:10:13,839
[Arguing In Ewokese]

879
01:10:13,922 --> 01:10:15,632
Hey!

880
01:10:15,716 --> 01:10:18,760
Han, don’t. It’ll be all right.

881
01:10:18,844 --> 01:10:21,138
[Speaking Ewokese]

882
01:10:24,892 --> 01:10:27,519
Chewie, give them your crossbow.

883
01:10:27,603 --> 01:10:29,521
Arrrrr!

884
01:10:29,605 --> 01:10:32,065
Oh, my head!

885
01:10:32,149 --> 01:10:35,402
[Speaking Ewokese]

886
01:10:35,485 --> 01:10:38,071
Oh, my goodness.

887
01:10:38,155 --> 01:10:41,491
[Speaking Ewokese]

888
01:10:44,494 --> 01:10:47,706
[Chanting In Ewokese]

889
01:11:02,054 --> 01:11:05,516
[Speaking Ewokese]

890
01:11:05,599 --> 01:11:08,185
[Speaking Ewokese]

891
01:11:08,435 --> 01:11:10,938
Do you understand anything they’re saying?

892
01:11:11,021 --> 01:11:12,606
Oh, yes, Master Luke.

893
01:11:12,689 --> 01:11:15,526
Remember that I am fluent
in over six million forms-

894
01:11:15,609 --> 01:11:18,779
What are you telling them?

895
01:11:18,862 --> 01:11:20,197
Hello, I think.

896
01:11:20,447 --> 01:11:21,782
I could be mistaken.

897
01:11:21,865 --> 01:11:24,201
They’re using a very primitive dialect.

898
01:11:24,451 --> 01:11:27,454
I do believe they think I am
some sort of god.

899
01:11:27,538 --> 01:11:28,956
[Beep Beep]

900
01:11:29,039 --> 01:11:30,207
Haaaar!

901
01:11:30,457 --> 01:11:36,088
Why don’t you use your divine influence
and get us out of this?

902
01:11:36,171 --> 01:11:39,091
I beg your pardon, General Solo,
but that just wouldn’t be proper.

903
01:11:39,174 --> 01:11:40,759
Proper?

904
01:11:40,843 --> 01:11:44,638
It’s against my programming
to impersonate a deity.

905
01:11:44,721 --> 01:11:45,681
Why, you-

906
01:11:45,764 --> 01:11:48,058
[Speaking Ewokese]

907
01:11:49,560 --> 01:11:52,563
[Speaking Ewokese]

908
01:11:53,814 --> 01:11:55,482
My mistake.

909
01:11:55,566 --> 01:11:57,484
He’s an old friend of mine.

910
01:11:57,568 --> 01:11:59,570
Jabba jabba jabba.

911
01:12:11,123 --> 01:12:13,208
♪
♪
♪

912
01:12:25,179 --> 01:12:26,513
Ow!

913
01:12:26,597 --> 01:12:28,599
Hey!

914
01:12:30,767 --> 01:12:32,561
[Squeak]

915
01:12:38,108 --> 01:12:39,693
Rrrr.

916
01:12:39,776 --> 01:12:41,111
Arrrr!

917
01:12:43,655 --> 01:12:47,159
I have a really bad feeling about this.

918
01:12:55,792 --> 01:12:59,671
[Speaking Ewokese]

919
01:13:03,133 --> 01:13:07,179
[Speaking Ewokese]

920
01:13:07,262 --> 01:13:09,223
What did he say?

921
01:13:09,306 --> 01:13:11,892
I’m rather embarrassed, General Solo,

922
01:13:11,975 --> 01:13:15,896
but it appears you are to be the main course
at a banquet in my honor.

923
01:13:15,979 --> 01:13:17,105
Arrrrr!

924
01:13:17,189 --> 01:13:20,317
[Singing In Ewokese]

925
01:13:27,824 --> 01:13:28,951
Leia!

926
01:13:29,034 --> 01:13:29,993
Leia!

927
01:13:30,077 --> 01:13:33,247
[Speaking Ewokese]

928
01:13:33,330 --> 01:13:35,832
Your Royal Highness.

929
01:13:35,916 --> 01:13:37,751
But these are my friends.

930
01:13:37,835 --> 01:13:40,712
[Singing In Ewokese]

931
01:13:40,796 --> 01:13:44,967
3PO, tell them they must be set free.

932
01:13:45,050 --> 01:13:46,677
Arrrrr!

933
01:13:46,760 --> 01:13:51,223
[Speaking Ewokese]

934
01:13:53,809 --> 01:13:56,854
[Speaking Ewokese]

935
01:13:56,937 --> 01:14:00,816
Eee! Ya! Ya! Ya!

936
01:14:00,899 --> 01:14:05,946
Somehow I got the feeling
that didn’t help us very much.

937
01:14:06,029 --> 01:14:10,075
3PO, tell them if they don’t do as you wish,

938
01:14:10,158 --> 01:14:12,077
you’ll become angry and use your magic.

939
01:14:12,160 --> 01:14:14,663
But, Master Luke, what magic?
I couldn’t possibly.

940
01:14:14,746 --> 01:14:16,206
Just tell them.

941
01:14:16,290 --> 01:14:19,251
[Speaking Ewokese]

942
01:14:23,714 --> 01:14:24,923
Boom!

943
01:14:25,007 --> 01:14:27,801
[Speaking Ewokese]

944
01:14:31,263 --> 01:14:35,976
You see, Master Luke? They didn’t believe me,
just as I said they wouldn’t.

945
01:14:36,059 --> 01:14:37,811
Wait, wait.

946
01:14:41,648 --> 01:14:44,234
Whoo! Whoo! Whoo! Whoo!

947
01:14:48,030 --> 01:14:48,947
Eee!

948
01:14:53,243 --> 01:14:55,037
Put me down!

949
01:14:55,120 --> 01:14:56,747
Help! Somebody!

950
01:14:56,830 --> 01:14:58,165
Somebody, help!

951
01:14:58,248 --> 01:15:00,751
Master Luke! R2, R2, quickly!

952
01:15:00,834 --> 01:15:01,960
Oh! Oh!

953
01:15:02,044 --> 01:15:04,421
[Speaking Ewokese]

954
01:15:18,268 --> 01:15:21,146
[Beep Beep Whistle]

955
01:15:23,857 --> 01:15:25,234
Oh!

956
01:15:25,317 --> 01:15:26,777
Aah!

957
01:15:26,860 --> 01:15:28,111
Ooh!
Ooh!

958
01:15:32,783 --> 01:15:34,159
Thank goodness.

959
01:15:39,289 --> 01:15:41,250
[Whistle Beep]

960
01:15:46,380 --> 01:15:48,131
Thanks, 3PO.

961
01:15:48,215 --> 01:15:51,009
I never knew I had it in me.

962
01:15:52,845 --> 01:15:57,182
Woochana makawartas,
woochana makawartas.

963
01:15:57,266 --> 01:15:59,393
Nervrenda bootootoo Tatooine.

964
01:15:59,476 --> 01:16:01,395
Faraway, mana quitoo.

965
01:16:01,478 --> 01:16:03,981
Princess Leia wasay wapa R2.

966
01:16:04,064 --> 01:16:06,233
Oos batata rundi Darth Vader!

967
01:16:06,316 --> 01:16:08,402
[Darth Vader’s Breathing]

968
01:16:08,485 --> 01:16:10,988
Un Chenko baskimo quertonto Death Star.

969
01:16:11,071 --> 01:16:12,823
[Roar Of Spaceship]

970
01:16:12,906 --> 01:16:14,783
[Zap]

971
01:16:14,867 --> 01:16:17,411
Wos michi un Jedi, Obi-Wan Kenobi.

972
01:16:17,494 --> 01:16:19,121
Ee manu machi Vader konyono.

973
01:16:19,204 --> 01:16:21,748
[Hum Of Lightsaber]

974
01:16:21,832 --> 01:16:23,417
[Whistle Whistle Beep Beep]

975
01:16:23,500 --> 01:16:25,419
Yes, R2, I was just coming to that.

976
01:16:25,502 --> 01:16:27,004
Torron togosh.

977
01:16:27,087 --> 01:16:28,881
[Feet Stomping]

978
01:16:28,964 --> 01:16:30,924
Master Luke ahchiminie choodoo.

979
01:16:31,008 --> 01:16:32,759
[Roar Of Spaceship]

980
01:16:32,843 --> 01:16:34,428
[Zap]

981
01:16:34,511 --> 01:16:36,430
Eee!

982
01:16:36,513 --> 01:16:39,391
Uta Millennium Falcon
ahchiminie Cloud City.

983
01:16:39,474 --> 01:16:41,268
[Roar Of Spaceship]

984
01:16:41,351 --> 01:16:43,770
Oos nooch Vader.

985
01:16:43,854 --> 01:16:44,938
[Darth Vader’s Breathing]

986
01:16:45,022 --> 01:16:46,273
Han Solo.

987
01:16:46,356 --> 01:16:47,441
Arrrr.

988
01:16:47,524 --> 01:16:49,943
Tiklo carbon!

989
01:16:50,027 --> 01:16:52,529
Un dekochna gooboo Sarlacc.

990
01:16:52,779 --> 01:16:54,531
[Lightsaber Crackling]

991
01:16:54,781 --> 01:16:56,158
Prrrrr.

992
01:16:56,241 --> 01:17:01,121
Haonna keenie chetoo toomoo maneta.

993
01:17:01,205 --> 01:17:05,042
[Speaking Ewokese]

994
01:17:14,343 --> 01:17:15,802
What’s going on?

995
01:17:15,886 --> 01:17:17,262
I don’t know.

996
01:17:19,556 --> 01:17:24,019
[Speaking Ewokese]

997
01:17:27,564 --> 01:17:29,983
[Speaking Ewokese]

998
01:17:30,067 --> 01:17:33,570
Wonderful.
We are now a part of the tribe.

999
01:17:34,905 --> 01:17:36,990
Just what I always wanted.

1000
01:17:37,074 --> 01:17:39,993
[Beep Beep Beep]

1001
01:17:48,961 --> 01:17:51,129
Short help’s better than no help at all.

1002
01:17:56,593 --> 01:18:00,305
He says the scouts are going to show us
the quickest way to the shield generator.

1003
01:18:00,389 --> 01:18:03,392
How far is it? Ask him.

1004
01:18:03,475 --> 01:18:05,894
We need some fresh supplies, too.

1005
01:18:05,978 --> 01:18:07,312
[Speaking Ewokese]

1006
01:18:07,396 --> 01:18:09,147
Try and get our weapons back.

1007
01:18:09,231 --> 01:18:10,524
[Speaking Ewokese]

1008
01:18:10,607 --> 01:18:13,902
Hurry up, will you? I haven’t got all day.

1009
01:18:14,987 --> 01:18:16,613
Luke, what’s wrong?

1010
01:18:18,240 --> 01:18:23,328
Leia, do you remember your mother,
your real mother?

1011
01:18:23,412 --> 01:18:28,250
Just a little bit.
She died when I was very young.

1012
01:18:28,333 --> 01:18:30,252
What do you remember?

1013
01:18:30,335 --> 01:18:32,212
Just images, really. Feelings.

1014
01:18:32,296 --> 01:18:33,630
Tell me.

1015
01:18:35,924 --> 01:18:37,259
She was...

1016
01:18:37,342 --> 01:18:39,261
very beautiful.

1017
01:18:39,344 --> 01:18:42,222
Kind...but sad.

1018
01:18:43,515 --> 01:18:46,643
Why are you asking me this?

1019
01:18:46,935 --> 01:18:50,230
I have no memory of my mother.

1020
01:18:50,314 --> 01:18:53,025
I never knew her.

1021
01:18:53,108 --> 01:18:56,987
Luke, tell me, what’s troubling you?

1022
01:19:01,158 --> 01:19:03,076
Vader is here.

1023
01:19:03,160 --> 01:19:05,120
Now. On this moon.

1024
01:19:07,122 --> 01:19:09,082
How do you know?

1025
01:19:09,166 --> 01:19:11,084
I felt his presence.

1026
01:19:11,168 --> 01:19:13,253
He’s come for me.

1027
01:19:13,337 --> 01:19:15,339
He can feel when I’m near.

1028
01:19:15,422 --> 01:19:17,216
That’s why I have to go.

1029
01:19:17,299 --> 01:19:22,095
As long as I stay, I’m endangering the group
and our mission here.

1030
01:19:22,179 --> 01:19:24,056
I have to face him.

1031
01:19:24,139 --> 01:19:25,516
Why?

1032
01:19:29,561 --> 01:19:31,522
He’s my father.

1033
01:19:34,358 --> 01:19:37,027
Your father?

1034
01:19:38,070 --> 01:19:39,404
There’s more.

1035
01:19:39,488 --> 01:19:42,616
It won’t be easy for you to hear it,
but you must.

1036
01:19:42,699 --> 01:19:46,119
If I don’t make it back,
you’re the only hope for the Alliance.

1037
01:19:46,203 --> 01:19:47,287
Don’t talk that way.

1038
01:19:47,371 --> 01:19:51,583
You have a power I don’t understand
and could never have.

1039
01:19:51,667 --> 01:19:53,418
You’re wrong, Leia.

1040
01:19:53,502 --> 01:19:56,046
You have that power, too.

1041
01:19:56,129 --> 01:20:01,051
In time, you’ll learn to use it as I have.

1042
01:20:03,554 --> 01:20:07,474
The Force is strong in my family.

1043
01:20:07,558 --> 01:20:09,434
My father has it.

1044
01:20:11,103 --> 01:20:13,021
I have it.

1045
01:20:13,105 --> 01:20:14,481
And...

1046
01:20:14,565 --> 01:20:17,317
my sister has it.

1047
01:20:24,074 --> 01:20:25,450
Yes.

1048
01:20:25,534 --> 01:20:27,452
It’s you, Leia.

1049
01:20:32,541 --> 01:20:34,084
I know.

1050
01:20:37,087 --> 01:20:39,298
Somehow...

1051
01:20:39,381 --> 01:20:42,301
I’ve always known.

1052
01:20:42,384 --> 01:20:44,344
Then you know why I have to face him.

1053
01:20:44,428 --> 01:20:48,098
No! Luke, run away. Far away.

1054
01:20:48,182 --> 01:20:51,768
If he can feel your presence,
then leave this place.

1055
01:20:52,060 --> 01:20:53,604
I wish I could go with you.

1056
01:20:53,687 --> 01:20:55,522
No, you don’t.

1057
01:20:55,606 --> 01:20:57,774
You’ve always been strong.

1058
01:20:58,025 --> 01:21:00,777
But why must you confront him?

1059
01:21:01,028 --> 01:21:03,780
Because... there is good in him.

1060
01:21:04,031 --> 01:21:05,365
I’ve felt it.

1061
01:21:05,449 --> 01:21:07,784
He won’t turn me over to the emperor.

1062
01:21:08,035 --> 01:21:09,369
I can save him.

1063
01:21:09,453 --> 01:21:12,331
I can turn him back to the good side.

1064
01:21:12,414 --> 01:21:13,790
I have to try.

1065
01:21:32,142 --> 01:21:34,311
Hey, what’s going on?

1066
01:21:34,394 --> 01:21:36,230
Nothing.

1067
01:21:36,313 --> 01:21:40,609
I just want to be alone for a little while.

1068
01:21:40,692 --> 01:21:42,653
Nothing?

1069
01:21:42,736 --> 01:21:44,321
Come on, tell me.

1070
01:21:44,404 --> 01:21:46,156
What’s going on?

1071
01:21:50,285 --> 01:21:51,578
I...

1072
01:21:51,662 --> 01:21:53,413
I can’t tell you.

1073
01:21:53,497 --> 01:21:55,415
Could you tell Luke?

1074
01:21:55,499 --> 01:21:58,418
Is that who you could tell?

1075
01:21:58,502 --> 01:22:00,420
I...

1076
01:22:00,504 --> 01:22:01,839
Ah.

1077
01:22:15,102 --> 01:22:16,436
I’m sorry.

1078
01:22:20,524 --> 01:22:21,859
Hold me.

1079
01:23:14,703 --> 01:23:17,706
This is the rebel that surrendered to us.

1080
01:23:17,789 --> 01:23:20,209
Although he denies it,
I believe there may be more of them,

1081
01:23:20,292 --> 01:23:23,629
and I request permission
to conduct a further search of the area.

1082
01:23:23,712 --> 01:23:26,465
He was armed only with this.

1083
01:23:28,717 --> 01:23:31,220
Good work, Commander.

1084
01:23:31,303 --> 01:23:32,679
Leave us.

1085
01:23:32,763 --> 01:23:38,352
Conduct your search
and bring his companions to me.

1086
01:23:38,435 --> 01:23:39,770
Yes, my lord.

1087
01:23:41,396 --> 01:23:44,233
The emperor has been expecting you.

1088
01:23:44,316 --> 01:23:46,860
I know, Father.

1089
01:23:46,944 --> 01:23:50,739
So, you have accepted the truth.

1090
01:23:50,822 --> 01:23:55,494
I’ve accepted the truth that you were once
Anakin Skywalker, my father.

1091
01:23:55,577 --> 01:23:58,747
That name no longer has any meaning for me.

1092
01:23:58,830 --> 01:24:02,376
It is the name of your true self.
You’ve only forgotten.

1093
01:24:02,459 --> 01:24:04,711
I know there is good in you.

1094
01:24:04,795 --> 01:24:08,298
The emperor hasn’t driven it from you fully.

1095
01:24:09,591 --> 01:24:12,886
That was why you couldn’t destroy me.

1096
01:24:12,970 --> 01:24:17,933
That’s why you won’t bring me
to your emperor now.

1097
01:24:22,980 --> 01:24:27,609
I see you have constructed a new lightsaber.

1098
01:24:31,280 --> 01:24:34,283
Your skills are complete.

1099
01:24:39,329 --> 01:24:43,959
Indeed you are powerful,
as the emperor has foreseen.

1100
01:24:48,005 --> 01:24:49,965
Come with me.

1101
01:24:52,009 --> 01:24:55,929
Obi-Wan once thought as you do.

1102
01:24:56,013 --> 01:25:01,393
You don’t know the power of the dark side.

1103
01:25:01,476 --> 01:25:03,562
I must obey my master.

1104
01:25:03,645 --> 01:25:09,026
I will not turn,
and you’ll be forced to kill me.

1105
01:25:09,318 --> 01:25:13,030
If that is your destiny.

1106
01:25:13,280 --> 01:25:16,658
Search your feelings, Father.
You can’t do this.

1107
01:25:16,742 --> 01:25:19,745
I feel the conflict within you.
Let go of your hate.

1108
01:25:19,828 --> 01:25:24,374
It is too late for me, son.

1109
01:25:26,710 --> 01:25:31,924
The emperor will show you
the true nature of the Force.

1110
01:25:32,007 --> 01:25:34,968
He is your master now.

1111
01:25:38,597 --> 01:25:41,725
Then my father is truly dead.

1112
01:26:07,042 --> 01:26:08,544
Urrr.

1113
01:26:24,017 --> 01:26:29,356
The main entrance to the control bunker
is on the far side of that landing platform.

1114
01:26:29,439 --> 01:26:31,441
This isn’t going to be easy.

1115
01:26:31,525 --> 01:26:32,860
Hey, don’t worry.

1116
01:26:32,943 --> 01:26:36,947
Chewie and me got into a lot of places
more heavily guarded than this.

1117
01:26:37,030 --> 01:26:39,867
[Speaking Ewokese]

1118
01:26:39,950 --> 01:26:42,119
[Speaking Ewokese]

1119
01:26:44,663 --> 01:26:46,915
[Leia]
What’s he saying?

1120
01:26:46,999 --> 01:26:50,627
He says there’s a secret entrance
on the other side of the ridge.

1121
01:27:09,646 --> 01:27:11,398
Admiral, we’re in position.

1122
01:27:11,481 --> 01:27:12,983
All fighters accounted for.

1123
01:27:13,066 --> 01:27:16,528
Proceed with the countdown.

1124
01:27:16,612 --> 01:27:19,573
All groups assume attack coordinates.

1125
01:27:19,656 --> 01:27:21,533
[Speaking Alien Language]

1126
01:27:21,617 --> 01:27:24,870
Don’t worry. My friend’s down there.

1127
01:27:24,953 --> 01:27:27,831
He’ll have that shield down on time.

1128
01:27:27,915 --> 01:27:29,458
[Speaking Alien Language]

1129
01:27:29,541 --> 01:27:33,921
Or this will be
the shortest offensive of all time.

1130
01:27:34,004 --> 01:27:38,717
All craft, prepare to jump
into hyperspace on my mark.

1131
01:27:38,800 --> 01:27:40,719
All right. Stand by.

1132
01:27:50,979 --> 01:27:52,731
[Whistle]

1133
01:27:58,529 --> 01:28:00,489
[Speaking Ewokese]

1134
01:28:00,572 --> 01:28:02,866
Back door, huh? Good idea.

1135
01:28:02,950 --> 01:28:05,118
[Speaking Ewokese]

1136
01:28:05,202 --> 01:28:08,872
[Speaking Ewokese]

1137
01:28:10,749 --> 01:28:13,836
It’s only a few guards.
This shouldn’t be too much trouble.

1138
01:28:13,919 --> 01:28:16,797
[Speaking Ewokese]

1139
01:28:16,880 --> 01:28:18,882
[Speaking Ewokese]

1140
01:28:18,966 --> 01:28:22,469
It only takes one to sound the alarm.

1141
01:28:22,553 --> 01:28:24,555
Then we’ll do it real quiet like.

1142
01:28:24,638 --> 01:28:26,974
Oh, my! Princess Leia!

1143
01:28:27,057 --> 01:28:32,563
I’m afraid our furry companion
has gone and done something rather rash.

1144
01:28:32,646 --> 01:28:34,481
Rrrrooohh.

1145
01:28:34,565 --> 01:28:36,483
Oh, no.

1146
01:28:36,567 --> 01:28:39,611
There goes our surprise attack.

1147
01:28:45,701 --> 01:28:47,077
[Starts Engine]

1148
01:28:47,160 --> 01:28:49,580
Look, over there! Stop him!

1149
01:29:00,215 --> 01:29:02,176
Not bad for a little furball.

1150
01:29:02,259 --> 01:29:03,802
There’s only one left.

1151
01:29:03,886 --> 01:29:05,179
You stay here.

1152
01:29:05,262 --> 01:29:07,014
We’ll take care of this.

1153
01:29:07,097 --> 01:29:11,268
I have decided
that we shall stay here.

1154
01:29:11,560 --> 01:29:13,187
Whoo-whoo!

1155
01:29:13,270 --> 01:29:14,271
Yahoo!

1156
01:29:18,692 --> 01:29:20,110
Whoo whoo!

1157
01:29:22,779 --> 01:29:25,240
Wa ha ha ha!

1158
01:29:34,124 --> 01:29:36,627
Wa ha ha ha!

1159
01:29:41,048 --> 01:29:42,174
Hey!

1160
01:29:48,305 --> 01:29:50,641
Yoooaww!

1161
01:29:51,892 --> 01:29:53,101
Ooohm.

1162
01:30:45,863 --> 01:30:48,949
Welcome, young Skywalker.

1163
01:30:49,032 --> 01:30:52,119
I have been expecting you.

1164
01:30:52,202 --> 01:30:54,705
You’ll no longer need those.

1165
01:30:59,835 --> 01:31:02,254
Guards, leave us.

1166
01:31:08,635 --> 01:31:13,265
I’m looking forward
to completing your training.

1167
01:31:13,348 --> 01:31:18,061
In time, you will call me master.

1168
01:31:18,145 --> 01:31:20,731
You’re gravely mistaken.

1169
01:31:20,814 --> 01:31:22,941
You won’t convert me as you did my father.

1170
01:31:23,025 --> 01:31:27,279
Oh, no, my young Jedi.

1171
01:31:29,156 --> 01:31:34,036
You will find that
it is you who are mistaken...

1172
01:31:35,078 --> 01:31:39,249
about a great many things.

1173
01:31:39,333 --> 01:31:41,793
His lightsaber.

1174
01:31:41,877 --> 01:31:46,340
Ah, yes. A Jedi’s weapon.

1175
01:31:46,423 --> 01:31:49,092
Much like your father’s.

1176
01:31:49,176 --> 01:31:54,806
By now you must know your father
can never be turned from the dark side.

1177
01:31:54,890 --> 01:31:57,809
So will it be with you.

1178
01:31:57,893 --> 01:31:59,186
You’re wrong.

1179
01:31:59,269 --> 01:32:02,940
Soon I’ll be dead, and you with me.

1180
01:32:03,023 --> 01:32:04,983
Ha ha ha ha!

1181
01:32:05,067 --> 01:32:10,739
Perhaps you refer
to the imminent attack of your rebel fleet.

1182
01:32:10,822 --> 01:32:12,950
Yes.

1183
01:32:13,033 --> 01:32:19,206
I assure you,
we are quite safe from your friends here.

1184
01:32:19,289 --> 01:32:22,209
Your overconfidence is your weakness.

1185
01:32:22,292 --> 01:32:26,713
Your faith in your friends is yours.

1186
01:32:26,797 --> 01:32:31,760
It is pointless to resist, my son.

1187
01:32:35,389 --> 01:32:40,894
Everything that has transpired
has done so according to my design.

1188
01:32:40,978 --> 01:32:49,945
Your friends up there on the sanctuary moon
are walking into a trap, as is your rebel fleet.

1189
01:32:50,028 --> 01:32:57,244
It was I who allowed the Alliance
to know the location of the shield generator.

1190
01:32:57,327 --> 01:33:01,081
It is quite safe from your pitiful little band.

1191
01:33:01,164 --> 01:33:05,377
An entire legion of my best troops awaits them.

1192
01:33:05,460 --> 01:33:07,254
Oh...

1193
01:33:07,337 --> 01:33:17,097
I’m afraid the deflector shield
will be quite operational when your friends arrive.

1194
01:33:20,184 --> 01:33:24,188
All right, up! Move! Come on.

1195
01:33:24,271 --> 01:33:25,856
Quickly. Quickly.

1196
01:33:25,939 --> 01:33:27,107
Chewie.

1197
01:33:27,191 --> 01:33:28,442
Grr!

1198
01:33:28,525 --> 01:33:30,152
Han, hurry!

1199
01:33:30,235 --> 01:33:34,156
The fleet will be here any moment.

1200
01:33:34,239 --> 01:33:37,242
Charges! Come on, come on!

1201
01:33:39,286 --> 01:33:41,163
Oh, my! They’ll be captured!

1202
01:33:41,246 --> 01:33:43,874
[Speaking Ewokese]

1203
01:33:43,957 --> 01:33:45,834
Wait! Wait! Come back!

1204
01:33:45,918 --> 01:33:48,128
[Speaking Ewokese]

1205
01:33:48,212 --> 01:33:50,088
R2, stay with me.

1206
01:33:50,172 --> 01:33:51,548
Freeze!

1207
01:33:52,883 --> 01:33:54,551
Aah!

1208
01:33:54,843 --> 01:33:56,803
You rebel scum.

1209
01:33:56,887 --> 01:33:59,097
Uhh waahh!

1210
01:33:59,181 --> 01:34:00,807
Uhh!

1211
01:34:00,891 --> 01:34:02,893
Ahh yaa!

1212
01:34:17,032 --> 01:34:18,992
All wings report in.

1213
01:34:19,076 --> 01:34:21,161
Red Leader standing by.

1214
01:34:21,245 --> 01:34:23,038
Gray Leader standing by.

1215
01:34:23,121 --> 01:34:25,332
Green Leader standing by.

1216
01:34:25,415 --> 01:34:28,335
Lock S-foils in attack positions.

1217
01:34:31,088 --> 01:34:34,842
May the Force be with us.

1218
01:34:34,925 --> 01:34:36,593
[Speaking Alien Language]

1219
01:34:36,885 --> 01:34:39,888
We’ve got to get a reading on that shield.

1220
01:34:39,972 --> 01:34:41,348
[Speaking Alien Language]

1221
01:34:41,431 --> 01:34:44,893
How could they be jamming us
if they don’t know...

1222
01:34:44,977 --> 01:34:46,854
if we’re coming.

1223
01:34:46,937 --> 01:34:48,355
Break off the attack!

1224
01:34:48,438 --> 01:34:50,357
The shield is still up.

1225
01:34:50,440 --> 01:34:53,277
I get no reading. You sure?

1226
01:34:53,360 --> 01:34:55,028
Pull up! All craft pull up!

1227
01:34:58,490 --> 01:35:00,200
Take evasive action.

1228
01:35:00,284 --> 01:35:03,370
Green Group, stick to Holding Sector MV-7.

1229
01:35:05,205 --> 01:35:08,041
Admiral, we have
enemy ships in Sector 47.

1230
01:35:08,125 --> 01:35:09,585
It’s a trap!

1231
01:35:13,172 --> 01:35:14,173
Fighters coming in!

1232
01:35:18,510 --> 01:35:20,053
There’s too many of them!

1233
01:35:23,265 --> 01:35:24,641
Accelerate to attack speed.

1234
01:35:24,933 --> 01:35:26,560
Draw their fire away from the cruisers.

1235
01:35:26,643 --> 01:35:27,978
Copy, Gold Leader.

1236
01:35:31,231 --> 01:35:33,233
Come, boy.

1237
01:35:33,317 --> 01:35:35,235
See for yourself.

1238
01:35:37,487 --> 01:35:43,410
From here, you will witness
the final destruction of the Alliance

1239
01:35:43,493 --> 01:35:47,414
and the end of your insignificant rebellion.

1240
01:35:51,919 --> 01:35:55,088
You want this...

1241
01:35:55,172 --> 01:35:57,591
don’t you?

1242
01:35:57,674 --> 01:36:02,304
The hate is swelling in you now.

1243
01:36:02,387 --> 01:36:05,265
Take your Jedi weapon.

1244
01:36:05,349 --> 01:36:07,059
Use it.

1245
01:36:07,142 --> 01:36:09,061
I am unarmed.

1246
01:36:09,144 --> 01:36:11,271
Strike me down with it.

1247
01:36:11,355 --> 01:36:14,942
Give in to your anger.

1248
01:36:15,025 --> 01:36:21,198
With each passing moment,
you make yourself more my servant.

1249
01:36:25,118 --> 01:36:26,495
No.

1250
01:36:26,578 --> 01:36:29,164
It is unavoidable.

1251
01:36:29,248 --> 01:36:32,042
It is your destiny.

1252
01:36:33,085 --> 01:36:36,004
You, like your father,

1253
01:36:36,088 --> 01:36:38,549
are now...

1254
01:36:38,632 --> 01:36:40,384
mine.

1255
01:36:57,734 --> 01:37:00,070
All right, move it!

1256
01:37:02,489 --> 01:37:05,075
Keep moving. Come on.

1257
01:37:07,369 --> 01:37:08,537
Hello!

1258
01:37:08,620 --> 01:37:10,497
I say, over there!

1259
01:37:10,581 --> 01:37:13,584
Were you looking for me?

1260
01:37:13,667 --> 01:37:14,751
Grr!

1261
01:37:15,043 --> 01:37:17,087
Bring those two down here.

1262
01:37:24,595 --> 01:37:25,762
Well, they’re on their way.

1263
01:37:26,054 --> 01:37:29,016
R2, are you sure this was a good idea?

1264
01:37:29,099 --> 01:37:30,100
Freeze!

1265
01:37:30,184 --> 01:37:31,602
Don’t move!

1266
01:37:31,685 --> 01:37:33,645
We surrender.

1267
01:37:33,729 --> 01:37:36,106
Aiyee!
Haa!

1268
01:37:44,364 --> 01:37:47,618
♪
♪ ♪

1269
01:37:47,701 --> 01:37:49,286
♪ ♪ ♪
♪

1270
01:37:49,369 --> 01:37:50,621
Whoo! Whoo!

1271
01:38:37,793 --> 01:38:40,170
Aiyee!
Yaah!

1272
01:39:07,531 --> 01:39:09,199
Aiyee!
Haa!

1273
01:39:39,396 --> 01:39:41,815
The code’s changed. We need R2.

1274
01:39:41,899 --> 01:39:43,692
Here’s the terminal.

1275
01:39:43,775 --> 01:39:47,905
R2, where are you?
We need you at the bunker right away.

1276
01:39:49,907 --> 01:39:51,533
What do you mean, you’re going?

1277
01:39:51,617 --> 01:39:53,202
[Bleep Boop]

1278
01:39:53,285 --> 01:39:54,828
Going where, R2?

1279
01:39:54,912 --> 01:39:56,371
No, wait!

1280
01:39:56,455 --> 01:39:58,832
This is no time for heroics!

1281
01:39:58,916 --> 01:40:00,918
Come back!

1282
01:40:27,277 --> 01:40:28,946
Watch yourself, Wedge. Three from above.

1283
01:40:29,238 --> 01:40:30,656
Red 3, Red 2, pull in.

1284
01:40:30,739 --> 01:40:32,241
Got it.

1285
01:40:35,369 --> 01:40:37,204
Three of them coming in, 20 degrees.

1286
01:40:37,287 --> 01:40:38,914
Cut to the left. I’ll take the leader.

1287
01:40:47,297 --> 01:40:48,966
They’re heading for the medical frigate.

1288
01:40:53,929 --> 01:40:55,305
Pressure steady.

1289
01:41:04,439 --> 01:41:05,732
Only the fighters are attacking.

1290
01:41:05,816 --> 01:41:07,693
I wonder what those Stardestroyers are waiting for.

1291
01:41:12,364 --> 01:41:13,991
We’re in attack position, sir.

1292
01:41:14,241 --> 01:41:14,992
Hold here.

1293
01:41:15,284 --> 01:41:16,577
We’re not going to attack?

1294
01:41:16,660 --> 01:41:18,620
I have my orders from the emperor himself.

1295
01:41:18,704 --> 01:41:20,581
He has something special planned for them.

1296
01:41:20,664 --> 01:41:22,833
We only need to keep them from escaping.

1297
01:41:24,251 --> 01:41:28,589
As you can see, my young apprentice,

1298
01:41:28,672 --> 01:41:31,884
your friends have failed.

1299
01:41:32,843 --> 01:41:40,726
Now witness the firepower of this
fully armed and operational battle station.

1300
01:41:41,727 --> 01:41:44,521
Fire at will, Commander.

1301
01:41:51,361 --> 01:41:52,362
Fire.

1302
01:41:57,993 --> 01:41:59,578
Oh!

1303
01:41:59,661 --> 01:42:03,040
That blast came from the Death Star.

1304
01:42:03,290 --> 01:42:05,542
That thing’s operational!

1305
01:42:05,626 --> 01:42:07,503
Home 1, this is Gold Leader.

1306
01:42:07,586 --> 01:42:09,671
All craft prepare to retreat.

1307
01:42:09,755 --> 01:42:11,965
You won’t get another chance at this, Admiral.

1308
01:42:12,049 --> 01:42:14,051
We have no choice, General Calrissian.

1309
01:42:14,301 --> 01:42:18,388
Our cruisers can’t repel
firepower of that magnitude.

1310
01:42:18,472 --> 01:42:19,973
Han will have that shield down.

1311
01:42:20,057 --> 01:42:22,059
We’ve got to give him more time.

1312
01:42:40,911 --> 01:42:42,496
We’re coming!

1313
01:42:45,791 --> 01:42:47,000
Aah!

1314
01:42:47,084 --> 01:42:49,419
Come on, come on!

1315
01:42:53,423 --> 01:42:54,800
Oh, R2, hurry!

1316
01:42:59,429 --> 01:43:00,681
Yeeoooww!

1317
01:43:00,764 --> 01:43:01,807
Oh, my goodness!

1318
01:43:03,684 --> 01:43:06,812
[Blip Blip Beep Beep]

1319
01:43:06,895 --> 01:43:09,857
Why did you have to be so brave?

1320
01:43:09,940 --> 01:43:11,859
Eeooow...

1321
01:43:11,942 --> 01:43:15,654
Well, I suppose I could hot-wire this thing.

1322
01:43:15,737 --> 01:43:17,114
I’ll cover you.

1323
01:43:39,386 --> 01:43:41,722
[Speaking Ewokese]

1324
01:43:43,932 --> 01:43:45,475
[Speaking Ewokese]

1325
01:43:58,739 --> 01:44:00,407
Yes, I said closer.

1326
01:44:00,490 --> 01:44:03,994
Move as close as you can and engage
those Stardestroyers at point-blank range!

1327
01:44:04,077 --> 01:44:07,623
At that close range, we won’t last long
against those Stardestroyers.

1328
01:44:07,706 --> 01:44:10,167
We’ll last longer than we will
against that Death Star!

1329
01:44:10,417 --> 01:44:12,753
And we might just take a few of them with us.

1330
01:44:15,672 --> 01:44:17,007
She’s going to blow!

1331
01:44:21,011 --> 01:44:22,721
I’m hit!

1332
01:44:26,934 --> 01:44:29,603
Your fleet is lost,

1333
01:44:29,686 --> 01:44:35,192
and your friends on the Endor moon
will not survive.

1334
01:44:35,484 --> 01:44:38,737
There is no escape...

1335
01:44:38,820 --> 01:44:41,198
my young apprentice.

1336
01:44:42,908 --> 01:44:46,203
The Alliance will die...

1337
01:44:48,080 --> 01:44:51,959
as will your friends.

1338
01:44:54,670 --> 01:44:56,797
Good.

1339
01:44:56,880 --> 01:45:01,802
I can feel your anger.

1340
01:45:01,885 --> 01:45:03,136
I am defenseless.

1341
01:45:03,220 --> 01:45:05,514
Take your weapon.

1342
01:45:05,597 --> 01:45:08,475
Strike me down with all of your hatred,

1343
01:45:08,559 --> 01:45:13,230
and your journey towards the dark side
will be complete!

1344
01:45:22,906 --> 01:45:25,909
Ha ha ha ha ha!

1345
01:45:29,955 --> 01:45:32,999
[Speaking Ewokese]

1346
01:45:45,095 --> 01:45:47,848
Ah...eeyaheeyah... eeyaheeyah!

1347
01:45:52,060 --> 01:45:52,978
Look!

1348
01:45:53,061 --> 01:45:55,564
Get him off of there!

1349
01:45:57,941 --> 01:45:59,109
Aaah!

1350
01:46:36,813 --> 01:46:39,608
Yahoo!

1351
01:46:39,691 --> 01:46:41,193
Yeeha! Yaaa!

1352
01:46:52,871 --> 01:46:54,164
Yeehaha!

1353
01:47:47,843 --> 01:47:49,845
I think I got it.

1354
01:47:49,928 --> 01:47:51,221
I got it!

1355
01:47:54,725 --> 01:47:56,101
Aah!

1356
01:47:58,395 --> 01:47:59,813
Princess Leia, are you all right?

1357
01:47:59,897 --> 01:48:00,814
Let’s see.

1358
01:48:00,898 --> 01:48:01,815
It’s not bad.

1359
01:48:01,899 --> 01:48:03,150
Freeze!
Oh, dear.

1360
01:48:03,233 --> 01:48:05,110
Don’t move!

1361
01:48:08,238 --> 01:48:10,741
I love you.

1362
01:48:10,824 --> 01:48:12,159
I know.

1363
01:48:12,242 --> 01:48:14,119
Hands up!

1364
01:48:14,203 --> 01:48:15,871
Stand up!

1365
01:48:25,714 --> 01:48:27,090
Stay back.

1366
01:48:31,136 --> 01:48:32,346
Arrr!

1367
01:48:32,429 --> 01:48:34,932
Chewie!

1368
01:48:35,015 --> 01:48:37,809
Get down here! She’s wounded!

1369
01:48:37,893 --> 01:48:39,770
No, wait!

1370
01:48:39,853 --> 01:48:41,355
I got an idea.

1371
01:48:52,241 --> 01:48:54,201
Good.

1372
01:48:54,284 --> 01:48:57,162
Use your aggressive feelings, boy.

1373
01:48:57,246 --> 01:49:01,041
Let the hate flow through you.

1374
01:49:05,838 --> 01:49:10,008
Obi-Wan has taught you well.

1375
01:49:13,762 --> 01:49:16,098
I will not fight you, Father.

1376
01:49:30,112 --> 01:49:33,740
You are unwise to lower your defenses.

1377
01:49:57,931 --> 01:50:00,267
Your thoughts betray you, Father.

1378
01:50:00,350 --> 01:50:03,520
I feel the good in you, the conflict.

1379
01:50:03,770 --> 01:50:06,148
There is no conflict.

1380
01:50:06,231 --> 01:50:10,152
You couldn’t bring yourself
to kill me before.

1381
01:50:10,235 --> 01:50:12,529
I don’t believe you’ll destroy me now.

1382
01:50:12,779 --> 01:50:17,242
You underestimate
the power of the dark side.

1383
01:50:17,326 --> 01:50:21,997
If you will not fight,
then you will meet your destiny.

1384
01:50:33,258 --> 01:50:36,094
[Emperor]
Good. Good.

1385
01:50:44,895 --> 01:50:47,147
Watch out! Squad at .06.

1386
01:50:47,231 --> 01:50:48,398
I’m on it, Gold Leader.

1387
01:50:50,317 --> 01:50:51,902
Good shot, Red 2.

1388
01:50:55,364 --> 01:50:56,990
We’re sure in the middle of it now.

1389
01:50:57,074 --> 01:51:00,285
Come on, Han, old buddy, don’t let me down.

1390
01:51:04,248 --> 01:51:06,208
It’s over, Commander.

1391
01:51:06,291 --> 01:51:08,836
The rebels have been routed.
They’re fleeing into the woods.

1392
01:51:08,919 --> 01:51:12,214
We need reinforcements
to continue the pursuit.

1393
01:51:12,297 --> 01:51:14,383
Send three squads to help.

1394
01:51:14,466 --> 01:51:16,468
Open the back door.

1395
01:51:30,107 --> 01:51:32,192
Throw me another charge.

1396
01:51:49,543 --> 01:51:52,880
You cannot hide forever, Luke.

1397
01:51:52,963 --> 01:51:55,465
I will not fight you.

1398
01:51:58,927 --> 01:52:02,222
Give yourself to the dark side.

1399
01:52:02,306 --> 01:52:08,896
It is the only way you can save your friends.

1400
01:52:08,979 --> 01:52:10,022
Yes.

1401
01:52:10,105 --> 01:52:12,024
Your thoughts betray you.

1402
01:52:12,107 --> 01:52:15,360
Your feelings for them are strong,

1403
01:52:15,444 --> 01:52:17,362
especially for...

1404
01:52:19,489 --> 01:52:21,116
sister.

1405
01:52:22,326 --> 01:52:23,410
So...

1406
01:52:23,493 --> 01:52:26,371
you have a twin sister.

1407
01:52:26,455 --> 01:52:30,584
Your feelings have now betrayed her, too.

1408
01:52:30,667 --> 01:52:34,463
Obi-Wan was wise to hide her from me.

1409
01:52:34,546 --> 01:52:39,343
Now his failure is complete.

1410
01:52:39,426 --> 01:52:43,972
If you will not turn to the dark side,

1411
01:52:44,056 --> 01:52:47,518
then perhaps she will.

1412
01:52:47,601 --> 01:52:48,560
Never!

1413
01:53:32,646 --> 01:53:33,981
Ha ha ha ha ha!

1414
01:53:34,064 --> 01:53:36,066
Good!

1415
01:53:40,279 --> 01:53:43,073
Your hate has made you powerful.

1416
01:53:43,156 --> 01:53:45,492
Now...

1417
01:53:45,576 --> 01:53:49,204
fulfill your destiny...

1418
01:53:49,288 --> 01:53:53,417
and take your father’s place at my side.

1419
01:54:08,182 --> 01:54:09,516
Never.

1420
01:54:11,602 --> 01:54:15,105
I’ll never turn to the dark side.

1421
01:54:18,025 --> 01:54:20,444
You’ve failed, Your Highness.

1422
01:54:20,527 --> 01:54:22,446
I am a Jedi,

1423
01:54:22,529 --> 01:54:26,116
like my father before me.

1424
01:54:32,039 --> 01:54:34,082
So be it...

1425
01:54:34,166 --> 01:54:36,168
Jedi.

1426
01:54:36,335 --> 01:54:37,544
Move!

1427
01:54:37,628 --> 01:54:38,795
Move!

1428
01:54:50,724 --> 01:54:52,267
The shield is down!

1429
01:54:52,351 --> 01:54:54,645
Commence attack
on the Death Star’s main reactor!

1430
01:54:54,728 --> 01:54:56,271
We’re on our way.

1431
01:54:56,355 --> 01:54:58,690
Red Group, Gold Group, all fighters follow me.

1432
01:54:58,774 --> 01:55:00,651
I told you they’d do it!

1433
01:55:07,157 --> 01:55:10,410
If you will not be turned,

1434
01:55:10,494 --> 01:55:13,830
you will be destroyed.

1435
01:55:20,212 --> 01:55:22,464
Young fool.

1436
01:55:22,548 --> 01:55:28,512
Only now, at the end,
do you understand.

1437
01:55:41,567 --> 01:55:47,447
Your feeble skills are no match
for the power of the dark side.

1438
01:55:49,741 --> 01:55:51,159
Aaah!

1439
01:55:51,243 --> 01:55:55,122
You have paid the price
for your lack of vision.

1440
01:55:55,205 --> 01:55:56,456
Aaah!

1441
01:56:00,711 --> 01:56:02,379
Father, please!

1442
01:56:02,462 --> 01:56:04,339
Ow! Aaah!

1443
01:56:07,259 --> 01:56:09,303
Help me!

1444
01:56:16,185 --> 01:56:17,561
Aaah!

1445
01:56:17,644 --> 01:56:19,897
Now, young Skywalker...

1446
01:56:21,607 --> 01:56:23,525
you will die.

1447
01:56:32,618 --> 01:56:34,745
Aahh!

1448
01:56:40,250 --> 01:56:41,877
Ow! Aaah!

1449
01:56:49,927 --> 01:56:51,595
No.

1450
01:56:53,639 --> 01:56:55,724
No!

1451
01:56:55,807 --> 01:56:57,768
Aaah!

1452
01:57:05,484 --> 01:57:08,570
Aaaahhhhh!

1453
01:57:19,748 --> 01:57:26,505
[Labored Breathing]

1454
01:57:46,650 --> 01:57:48,277
I’m going in.

1455
01:57:51,321 --> 01:57:52,573
Here goes nothing.

1456
01:57:59,580 --> 01:58:01,331
Now lock onto the strongest power source.

1457
01:58:01,415 --> 01:58:03,542
It should be the power generator.

1458
01:58:05,669 --> 01:58:07,337
Form up. Stay alert.

1459
01:58:07,421 --> 01:58:09,298
We could run out of space real fast.

1460
01:58:24,771 --> 01:58:26,773
Split up and head back to the surface.

1461
01:58:26,857 --> 01:58:30,027
See if you can get a few
of those TIE fighters to follow you.

1462
01:58:30,319 --> 01:58:31,361
Copy, Gold Leader.

1463
01:58:41,538 --> 01:58:43,040
That was too close.

1464
01:58:47,002 --> 01:58:49,338
We’ve got to give those fighters more time.

1465
01:58:49,421 --> 01:58:52,508
Concentrate all fire
on that Super Stardestroyer.

1466
01:58:58,388 --> 01:59:00,682
Sir, we’ve lost our bridge deflector shields.

1467
01:59:00,766 --> 01:59:02,309
Intensify the forward batteries.

1468
01:59:02,392 --> 01:59:03,810
I don’t want anything to get through!

1469
01:59:06,396 --> 01:59:07,981
Intensify forward firepower!

1470
01:59:08,065 --> 01:59:09,775
Aaah!

1471
01:59:09,858 --> 01:59:11,777
Too late!

1472
01:59:19,076 --> 01:59:21,495
[Cheering And Applause]

1473
01:59:54,111 --> 01:59:55,612
Luke.

1474
01:59:55,696 --> 02:00:00,033
Help me take this mask off.

1475
02:00:00,117 --> 02:00:02,828
But you’ll die.

1476
02:00:02,911 --> 02:00:07,040
Nothing can stop that now.

1477
02:00:07,124 --> 02:00:09,126
Just for once...

1478
02:00:09,376 --> 02:00:15,132
let me look on you with my own eyes.

1479
02:00:51,168 --> 02:00:53,086
Now...

1480
02:00:53,170 --> 02:00:56,006
go, my son.

1481
02:00:57,174 --> 02:00:58,717
Leave me.

1482
02:00:59,927 --> 02:01:01,929
No. You’re coming with me.

1483
02:01:02,012 --> 02:01:05,057
I’ll not leave you here. I’ve got to save you.

1484
02:01:05,140 --> 02:01:09,728
You already have, Luke.

1485
02:01:09,811 --> 02:01:12,773
You were right.

1486
02:01:12,856 --> 02:01:15,651
You were right about me.

1487
02:01:17,194 --> 02:01:20,572
Tell your sister...

1488
02:01:20,656 --> 02:01:23,033
you were right.

1489
02:01:29,039 --> 02:01:31,041
Father.

1490
02:01:35,212 --> 02:01:36,755
I won’t leave you.

1491
02:02:02,072 --> 02:02:03,073
There it is.

1492
02:02:06,034 --> 02:02:08,537
All right, Wedge,
go for the power regulator on the north tower.

1493
02:02:08,620 --> 02:02:11,915
Copy, Gold Leader.
I’m already on my way out.

1494
02:02:31,059 --> 02:02:34,229
Move the fleet away from the Death Star.

1495
02:03:01,215 --> 02:03:02,716
Yee-ha!

1496
02:03:02,799 --> 02:03:03,759
Yah.

1497
02:03:16,772 --> 02:03:19,066
Yaaa!
Ya!

1498
02:03:19,149 --> 02:03:21,235
[Beep! Beep! Beep!]

1499
02:03:21,318 --> 02:03:23,153
They did it!

1500
02:03:30,744 --> 02:03:34,039
I’m sure Luke
wasn’t on that thing when it blew.

1501
02:03:35,666 --> 02:03:37,751
He wasn’t.

1502
02:03:37,835 --> 02:03:40,337
I can feel it.

1503
02:03:43,757 --> 02:03:45,759
You love him.

1504
02:03:48,303 --> 02:03:50,597
Don’t you?

1505
02:03:50,681 --> 02:03:52,057
Yes.

1506
02:03:52,140 --> 02:03:54,935
All right. I understand.

1507
02:03:55,018 --> 02:03:57,271
Fine.

1508
02:03:57,354 --> 02:03:59,273
When he comes back,

1509
02:03:59,356 --> 02:04:02,067
I won’t get in the way.

1510
02:04:03,318 --> 02:04:06,822
It’s not like that at all.

1511
02:04:09,867 --> 02:04:11,827
He’s my brother.

1512
02:04:28,302 --> 02:04:30,220
[Speaking Ewokese]

1513
02:04:41,023 --> 02:04:44,985
♪
♪

1514
02:05:54,179 --> 02:05:56,390
Wesa free!

1515
02:06:27,921 --> 02:06:29,840
[Singing In Ewokese]

